1
00:01:15,220 --> 00:01:16,220
船长
Captain

2
00:01:16,860 --> 00:01:17,870
船长
Captain

3
00:01:37,690 --> 00:01:39,460
你是谁?
Who are you?

4
00:02:32,450 --> 00:02:33,640
怎么回事?
What is this?

5
00:02:33,780 --> 00:02:37,310
陛下 他是渔网捞起来的 渔网
Your Majesty, caught him up\nin a fishing net. A fishing net.

6
00:02:37,450 --> 00:02:39,390
陛下 他一直在讲故事\n故事里...
Sire, he's been telling stories.\nStories that...

7
00:02:39,520 --> 00:02:41,460
我们相信他找到了...
We believe he's found a...

8
00:02:49,430 --> 00:02:51,360
庞德・里昂\n(西班牙探险家 在寻找不老泉的路上发现了弗罗里达)
Ponce de León

9
00:02:53,540 --> 00:02:55,830
说他找到了\n庞德・里昂的船
Says he found\nPonce de León's ship.

10
00:02:55,970 --> 00:02:58,700
- 或是一起行过船\n- 不 我跟你说了
- Or sailed on it.\n- No, I told you,

11
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:01,140
庞德・里昂200年前就死了
Ponce de León died 200 years ago.

12
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:04,800
好 但他就是因为找什么东西才死的 \n没错吧?
Aye, but he died searching\nfor something, didn't he?

13
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:09,210
不老泉
The Fountain of Youth.

14
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:16,090
你多快能起航?
How soon can you sail?

15
00:03:17,390 --> 00:03:19,520
涨潮就行
With the tide.

16
00:03:23,390 --> 00:03:30,920
加勒比海盗4:惊涛怪浪

17
00:03:37,580 --> 00:03:38,770
看这里!\n幸运草!
Over here!\nLucky heather!

18
00:03:40,010 --> 00:03:41,980
海盗剑!海盗剑!
Pirate swords! Pirate swords!

19
00:03:42,150 --> 00:03:45,550
海盗于今天处决\n来看他被绞死!
Pirate's execution today.\nWatch him swing!

20
00:03:45,690 --> 00:03:47,550
海盗木偶!
Pirate puppets!

21
00:03:48,190 --> 00:03:49,210
吃我一剑 你!
Take that, you!

22
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:51,190
快点 爸爸 要不我们就看不见绞刑了!
Hurry, Papa, or we'll miss the hanging!

23
00:03:51,290 --> 00:03:54,990
这不是绞刑 宝贝 是公审\n下午才是绞刑
It's not a hanging, dear, it's a trial.\nThe hanging comes this afternoon.

24
00:03:55,160 --> 00:03:56,790
海盗今天被绞死!
Pirate hanging today!

25
00:03:58,730 --> 00:04:01,630
来啊 往上来
Come on. Up you get.

26
00:04:02,740 --> 00:04:04,530
挪过去 海盗
Move along, pirate.

27
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:08,070
或者我应该说 "海盗船长"?
Or should I say, "Captain Pirate"?

28
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:12,440
过来 过来 往上走
Come on. Come on! Up you go.

29
00:04:12,580 --> 00:04:14,450
肃静! 秩序!
Quiet! Order!

30
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:17,320
肃静!
Quiet!

31
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,920
现在出现在法庭前的
Now appearing before the court,

32
00:04:20,050 --> 00:04:23,290
这就是声名狼藉的邪恶海盗 掠夺者
the notorious and infamous\npirate, pillager,

33
00:04:23,420 --> 00:04:24,820
- 还有强盗...\n- 安静!
- and highwayman...\n- Quiet!

34
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:26,650
...杰克・斯派洛船长!
...Captain Jack Sparrow!

35
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:34,430
我跟你说了 名字是吉布斯!\n乔士米・吉布斯!
I told you, the name's Gibbs!\nJoshamee Gibbs!

36
00:04:34,570 --> 00:04:36,370
- 多少次才...\n- 听到了 听到了!
- How many times...\n- Hear ye, hear ye!

37
00:04:36,540 --> 00:04:37,830
全体起立迎接 主持审判的
Presiding over these trials,

38
00:04:37,970 --> 00:04:43,600
正义崇高的史密斯法官!
all rise and attend,\nthe Right Honorable Justice Smith!

39
00:04:53,250 --> 00:04:55,150
尊敬的阁下
My dear sir.

40
00:04:58,330 --> 00:05:00,120
安静!
Quiet!

41
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:03,690
好了...
Now...

42
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:07,070
...堂下是何人?
...what do we have here?

43
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:08,530
杰克?
Jack?

44
00:05:08,670 --> 00:05:10,160
闭嘴!
Shut up!

45
00:05:11,010 --> 00:05:11,970
我不认识他
I don't recognize him.

46
00:05:12,110 --> 00:05:15,300
没这必要 你说什么?
Not necessary. You were saying?

47
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:18,070
我不是杰克・斯派洛
Jack Sparrow is not my name.

48
00:05:18,250 --> 00:05:20,150
我叫乔士米・吉布斯!
My name is Joshamee Gibbs.

49
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:22,010
是这样么?
Is that so?

50
00:05:22,150 --> 00:05:25,180
- 这里写的是杰克・斯派洛\n- 我告诉他们
- It says Jack Sparrow here.\n- I told 'em.

51
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:28,480
我不是杰克・斯派洛\n我倒是很乐意在法庭上指证他
I'm not Jack Sparrow, who I would\nbe happy to identify to the court

52
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:31,520
- 如果那对我的案子有所帮助的话\n- 这真是可悲的狡辩啊
- if it would help my case.\n- I think that would be a poor defense,

53
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:34,360
除非你想像只大海豹那样被击倒
unless you want to be bludgeoned again\nlike a harp seal.

54
00:05:36,060 --> 00:05:37,660
犯人声称自己
The prisoner claims of being innocent

55
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:40,200
不是杰克・斯派洛\n你们的裁决如何?
to being Jack Sparrow. How do you find?

56
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,060
不公审? 但我们不是来这里检验证据的吗...
No trial? But aren't we here\nto examine the evidence...

57
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:45,730
陪审团长 你觉得他有罪吗?
Foreman, your finding. Guilty?

58
00:05:45,870 --> 00:05:47,740
有罪裁决意味着他要被绞死
Guilty verdict means he'll hang.

59
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:51,570
绞死他! 把他吊起来!
Hang him! String him up!

60
00:05:54,350 --> 00:05:56,370
- 有罪?\n- 这不公平!
- Guilty?\n- That's not fair!

61
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:57,750
闭嘴
Shut it.

62
00:05:59,090 --> 00:06:02,780
乔士米・吉布斯 你作为杰克・斯派洛
Joshamee Gibbs, the crime of which\nyou've been found guilty of

63
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:05,690
被指控的罪行是无辜的
is being innocent of being Jack Sparrow.

64
00:06:06,430 --> 00:06:08,220
我在此减免你的判刑
I hereby commute your sentence,

65
00:06:08,360 --> 00:06:11,030
判你无期徒刑
and order that you be imprisoned\nfor the remainder

66
00:06:11,170 --> 00:06:14,030
在牢里度过你那可悲的 垂死的 \n水深火热的余生吧
of your miserable, moribund,\nmutton-chopped life.

67
00:06:14,170 --> 00:06:16,100
- 什么?!\n- 绞死他!
- What?!\n- Hang him!

68
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:17,430
- 绞死他!\n- 就这样了
- Hang him!\n- There.

69
00:06:18,170 --> 00:06:20,940
- 胡扯!\n- 吊死他! 吊得高高的!
- Balderdash!\n- String him up! Hang him high!

70
00:06:22,580 --> 00:06:25,240
之后会安排押送这名犯人
Means shall be arranged\nto transport this prisoner

71
00:06:25,380 --> 00:06:27,410
去伦敦塔
to the Tower of London.

72
00:06:38,790 --> 00:06:40,230
非常感谢
Thanks very much.

73
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,790
谢谢
Ta.

74
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:52,230
快 滚上去
Come on. Get up there.

75
00:06:54,610 --> 00:06:56,370
上去!
Get up!

76
00:07:01,050 --> 00:07:04,710
该死的\n现在我们都奔监狱去了
Hell's teeth.\nNow we're both headed for prison.

77
00:07:04,820 --> 00:07:07,520
别担心\n我买通了马夫
Not to worry.\nI've paid off the driver.

78
00:07:07,690 --> 00:07:11,060
十分钟后 我们就到伦敦城外\n马已经在等我们了
Ten minutes, we'll be outside\nLondon Town, horses waiting.

79
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:12,720
今晚 我们就能到海岸
Tonight, we make the coast.

80
00:07:12,830 --> 00:07:15,190
然后就只剩找艘船了
Then it's just a matter\nof finding a ship.

81
00:07:16,460 --> 00:07:19,130
- 全在计划之中 对么?\n- 完全正确
- All part of the plan, yes?\n- Exactly.

82
00:07:19,270 --> 00:07:21,200
我今早才到达伦敦城的
I arrived in London Town\njust this morning

83
00:07:21,370 --> 00:07:24,500
为解救那个乔士米・吉布斯\n和绞架有约的人
to rescue one Joshamee Gibbs\nfrom one appointment with the gallows.

84
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:26,440
看见你现在还活着
Seeing as how you're still alive,

85
00:07:26,570 --> 00:07:29,300
我得说至今为止一切都很顺利
I'd say it's all been\nvery successful thus far.

86
00:07:29,980 --> 00:07:31,170
你怎么了 吉布斯?
What happened to you, Gibbs?

87
00:07:31,310 --> 00:07:33,870
我以为你任职他处或是转行了呢
I thought you were employed elsewhere\nor otherwise engaged.

88
00:07:34,050 --> 00:07:37,510
是啊 但我总是像贼一样\n偷听有关黑珍珠号的消息
Aye. But I always listened like a thief\nfor news of the Black Pearl.

89
00:07:37,650 --> 00:07:40,120
没人知道她要驶向何方
Nobody's seen where\nshe might next make port.

90
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:42,310
然后 我听到谣传:
Then, I hear a rumor:

91
00:07:42,460 --> 00:07:45,950
杰克・斯派洛在伦敦招募新人员上船
Jack Sparrow's in London\nwith a ship and looking for a crew.

92
00:07:46,090 --> 00:07:47,820
- 我没有啊\n- 但我听说的是这样
- Am not.\n- But that's what I heard.

93
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:50,190
事实上 你今晚就要在
Fact is, you're signing up men tonight.

94
00:07:50,330 --> 00:07:51,860
叫"船长的女儿"的酒吧签人
Pub called The Captain's Daughter.

95
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:55,230
- 我没有!\n- 嗯 我觉得这事有点怪
- Am not!\n- Well, I thought it a bit odd,

96
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:59,100
但然后 你从来都不按常理出牌
but then, you've never been\nthe most predictable of sorts.

97
00:07:59,970 --> 00:08:01,240
告诉我
Tell me something.

98
00:08:01,410 --> 00:08:04,900
是不是有人在借我的名字\n在外面玷污我的名声?
There is another Jack Sparrow out there\nsullying my good name?

99
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:07,210
- 骗子\n- 没错
- An impostor.\n- Indeed.

100
00:08:07,350 --> 00:08:11,110
但是...是一个有船的骗子
But... an impostor with a ship.

101
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:13,810
需要人手
And in need of a crew.

102
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,980
此乃天助我也 我也如此
Which, as fate would have it, so am I.

103
00:08:16,990 --> 00:08:18,580
你怎么样 杰克?
What about you, Jack?

104
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:22,590
上次我听说\n你固执的要找到不老泉
Last I heard, you were hell-bent\nto find the Fountain of Youth.

105
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:24,250
运气如何?
Any luck?

106
00:08:26,330 --> 00:08:29,270
遇到了状况\n我们不得不...
Circumstances arose\nand forced a compelling insight

107
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,410
先英勇救人
regarding discretion and valor.

108
00:08:31,540 --> 00:08:34,670
- 那就是说你放弃了\n- 我没有
- Meaning, you gave up.\n- I did not.

109
00:08:34,810 --> 00:08:37,610
我只是和以往一样一心不二\n极其确定
I am just as bent as ever.\nHellishly so.

110
00:08:37,780 --> 00:08:42,580
我会尝到那些水的\n吉布斯船长 记着我的话
I shall taste those waters,\nMaster Gibbs. Mark my words.

111
00:08:45,350 --> 00:08:46,380
挺近啊
Short trip.

112
00:08:55,260 --> 00:08:58,360
都在计划之中 对么?
All part of the plan, yes?

113
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:02,560
不对
No.

114
00:10:30,890 --> 00:10:34,050
你就是杰克・斯派洛?
You are Jack Sparrow?

115
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:36,790
还应该有个"船长"
There should be a "Captain"\nin there somewhere.

116
00:10:36,930 --> 00:10:39,460
我听说过你
I've heard of you.

117
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,660
你也知道我是谁
And you know who I am.

118
00:10:42,670 --> 00:10:45,260
看起来面熟\n我以前勒索过你么?
Face is familiar.\nHave I threatened you before?

119
00:10:45,370 --> 00:10:49,170
在你面前的是乔治・奥古斯特斯\n布朗斯维克-鲁纳伯格的公爵
You are in the presence of George\nAugustus, Duke of Brunswick-Luneburg,

120
00:10:49,310 --> 00:10:52,180
和神圣的罗马帝国财务大臣和选帝侯
Archtreasurer and Prince-elector\nof the Holy Roman Empire,

121
00:10:52,310 --> 00:10:55,710
大不列颠和爱尔兰的国王\n还是你的王
King of Great Britain and Ireland,\nand of you.

122
00:10:57,180 --> 00:10:59,550
- 没印象\n- 我得知
- Doesn't ring a bell.\n- I am informed

123
00:10:59,690 --> 00:11:04,150
你来伦敦为你的船招募人手
you have come to London\nto procure a crew for your ship.

124
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:06,430
恶毒的谣言 不是真的
Vicious rumor. Not true.

125
00:11:06,590 --> 00:11:09,690
那刚才你说你是杰克・斯派洛就是骗我咯
Then you lied to me when you\ntold me you were Jack Sparrow.

126
00:11:09,830 --> 00:11:13,060
我是杰克・斯派洛\n但我不是来这儿找人手的
I am Jack Sparrow,\nbut I'm not here to procure a crew.

127
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:15,630
那是... 别的人
That is... someone else.

128
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:20,330
别的叫杰克・斯派洛的人
Someone else named Jack Sparrow.

129
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:23,240
你们带错人了 害我白跑一趟了
You've brought me the wrong wastrel.

130
00:11:23,380 --> 00:11:26,680
找到那个真的 把这个冒牌货干掉
Find the proper one\nand dispose of this impostor.

131
00:11:26,810 --> 00:11:28,870
不 等等 等等 等等 别急
No, wait, wait, wait. Hang on a minute.

132
00:11:29,020 --> 00:11:31,420
我是独一无二的杰克・斯派洛
I'm Jack Sparrow, the one and only.

133
00:11:31,550 --> 00:11:33,250
我是在伦敦
And I am in London.

134
00:11:33,390 --> 00:11:35,450
招人手
To procure a crew.

135
00:11:35,620 --> 00:11:37,320
准备起航去找
To undertake a voyage

136
00:11:37,430 --> 00:11:38,890
- 不老泉...\n- 什么?
- to the Fountain...\n- What?

137
00:11:39,030 --> 00:11:43,590
谁来把这些可恶的链子拿掉吧
Will someone please remove\nthese infernal chains?

138
00:11:43,730 --> 00:11:44,890
来 来
Come, come.

139
00:11:47,370 --> 00:11:49,770
我们知道你手上拿着地图
We know you're in possession of a map.

140
00:11:49,900 --> 00:11:53,070
没收地图 然后绞了他!
So confiscate the map,\nand to the gallows with him!

141
00:11:53,210 --> 00:11:55,070
你有地图么?
Have you a map?

142
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:02,450
- 没\n- 在哪儿?
- No.\n- Where is it?

143
00:12:02,580 --> 00:12:06,280
真话? 我弄丢了
The truth? I lost it.

144
00:12:06,420 --> 00:12:10,410
- 事实上 就在最近\n- 我有一份报告
- Quite recently, in fact.\n- I have a report.

145
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:14,150
西班牙人找到了不老泉
The Spanish have located\nthe Fountain of Youth.

146
00:12:14,330 --> 00:12:19,430
我不会让那悲哀的西班牙君主
I will not have some\nmelancholy Spanish monarch,

147
00:12:19,570 --> 00:12:24,160
一个天主教徒 得到永生的!
a Catholic, gain eternal life!

148
00:12:26,270 --> 00:12:28,710
你确实知道去不老泉的路?
You do know the way to the Fountain?

149
00:12:28,810 --> 00:12:30,970
我当然知道\n看看我
Of course I do.\nLook at me.

150
00:12:31,110 --> 00:12:32,980
你能带领一支探险队么
You could guide an expedition.

151
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:37,640
只要你允许 陛下
With your permission, your heinie,

152
00:12:37,790 --> 00:12:40,190
你会给我补给 船...
you will be providing, then, a ship...

153
00:12:42,090 --> 00:12:43,450
...还有船员?
...and a crew?

154
00:12:43,590 --> 00:12:46,120
还有一位船长
And a captain.

155
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:03,970
下午好 陛下
Afternoon, sire.

156
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:09,350
容我大胆问一句\n为什么这人没有被链子锁起来?
If I may be so bold,\nwhy is that man not in chains?

157
00:13:09,480 --> 00:13:11,420
他必须被马上锁起来
He must be manacled at once.

158
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:15,150
在我宫殿的中心? 他没啥威胁的
At the center of my palace? Hardly.

159
00:13:15,290 --> 00:13:17,450
海克特
Hector.

160
00:13:17,590 --> 00:13:21,080
很高兴看到一个海盗弃暗投明
How nice to see a fellow pirate\nmake good of himself.

161
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:24,360
海盗? 不对 是私掠船
Pirate? Nay. Privateer.

162
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:30,100
执行的是受吾王批准和保护的任务
On a sanctioned mission under the\nauthority and protection of the Crown.

163
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:33,700
可能吧 但首先
As may be, but first,

164
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:36,040
我那亲爱的珍珠号怎么样了?
what has become of my beloved Pearl?

165
00:13:36,180 --> 00:13:39,310
我丢了珍珠号和我的腿
I lost the Pearl as I lost my leg.

166
00:13:39,450 --> 00:13:41,710
- 珍珠号丢了?\n- 是
- Lost the Pearl?\n- Aye.

167
00:13:41,850 --> 00:13:45,790
我奋力的保护她\n尽管如此 她还是沉了
I defended her mightily enough,\nbut she be sunk nonetheless.

168
00:13:52,430 --> 00:13:55,880
如果那艘船就这么沉了\n你也应该和她一起沉了
If that ship be sunk properly,\nyou should be sunk with it.

169
00:13:56,030 --> 00:14:01,330
巴博萨船长 我们每耽误一秒\n西班牙人就甩开我们多一些
Captain Barbossa, each second we tarry,\nthe Spanish outdistance us.

170
00:14:01,470 --> 00:14:04,900
我很有信心你会得胜还朝并被嘉奖
I have every confidence\nyou will prevail and be rewarded

171
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:07,370
你渴望已久的高位
with the high station you so desire.

172
00:14:07,510 --> 00:14:12,280
- 能为您服务就够了 陛下\n- 而你 先生 堕落了
- To serve doth suffice, sire.\n- You, sir, have stooped.

173
00:14:13,380 --> 00:14:15,750
杰克 你的时间不多了
Jack, our sands be all but run.

174
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:19,220
何不加入赢者的队列呢?
Where's the harm\nin joining the winning side?

175
00:14:19,350 --> 00:14:23,150
你也能和王公贵族接触
And you do meet\na nicer class of person.

176
00:14:23,260 --> 00:14:25,690
我都明白
I understand everything.

177
00:14:27,030 --> 00:14:28,390
除了那假发
Except that wig.

178
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:37,860
他要逃了!\n拦住他!
He's getting away!\nStop him!

179
00:14:38,010 --> 00:14:41,600
- 射他的头!\n- 不! 拦住那海盗!
- Head him off!\n- No! Stop that pirate!

180
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:04,590
下来!
Come down!

181
00:15:14,840 --> 00:15:18,280
- 他逃了?\n- 交给我吧 陛下
- He escaped?\n- Leave it to me, sire.

182
00:15:23,750 --> 00:15:27,120
守卫! 守卫!
Guards! Guards!

183
00:15:49,940 --> 00:15:52,380
- 武器准备!\n- 好 先生!
- Arms at ready!\n- Aye, sir!

184
00:15:59,320 --> 00:16:00,910
找到他!
Find him!

185
00:16:22,810 --> 00:16:24,610
寻卫员 看守员!
Finders keepers!

186
00:16:24,710 --> 00:16:25,970
在那儿!
There!

187
00:16:49,470 --> 00:16:50,770
就完了?
Is that it?

188
00:16:55,140 --> 00:16:57,440
停! 停下马车!
Halt! Stop that carriage!

189
00:16:57,610 --> 00:16:58,870
射他的头!
Head him off!

190
00:17:07,890 --> 00:17:09,520
让开路!
Out of the way!

191
00:17:36,350 --> 00:17:38,550
拦住那个海盗!
Stop that pirate!

192
00:17:40,690 --> 00:17:42,250
把路让开!
Move out of the way!

193
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,220
拦住那人!
Stop that man!

194
00:17:51,670 --> 00:17:52,890
别让他逃了!
Don't let him get away!

195
00:18:00,810 --> 00:18:02,140
开火!
Fire!

196
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:33,770
他要逃了!\n追他! 拦住他!
He's getting away!\nAfter him! Stop him!

197
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:38,640
追上他!
After him!

198
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:51,420
肮脏的海盗
Filthy pirate.

199
00:19:01,340 --> 00:19:03,670
你好啊 小杰
Hello, Jackie.

200
00:19:06,310 --> 00:19:07,860
你好啊 爸爸
Hello, Dad.

201
00:19:15,820 --> 00:19:18,480
我听说你正在招人
I heard you're putting together a crew.

202
00:19:18,620 --> 00:19:21,490
如果大家都这么说 那一定是真的了
If enough people keep saying it,\nit must be true.

203
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:24,390
我知道你要去哪儿\n不老泉
I heard where you're headed.\nThe Fountain.

204
00:19:24,530 --> 00:19:26,020
你去过?
Have you been there?

205
00:19:26,960 --> 00:19:30,190
你看这张脸像是去过不老泉的么?
Does this face look like\nit's been to the Fountain of Youth?

206
00:19:31,630 --> 00:19:34,830
- 这要看灯光了\n- 儿子 去到那泉
- Depends on the light.\n- Son, the Fountain.

207
00:19:34,970 --> 00:19:38,800
需要有指定的物品\n才能完成凡俗的仪式
There'll be items required\nfor the profane ritual.

208
00:19:38,910 --> 00:19:40,570
两个圣杯
Two chalices.

209
00:19:41,340 --> 00:19:44,740
- 在地图上画了圣杯\n- 两个 银质的
- On the map there was a chalice.\n- Two, silver.

210
00:19:44,880 --> 00:19:47,750
来自于庞德・里昂的船上\n你两个都需要\nFrom the Ponce de Len ship.
You'll need both.

211
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:51,510
- 干吗?\n- 做仪式 别当傻子 小杰
- For?\n- The ritual. Don't be a fool, Jackie.

212
00:19:51,650 --> 00:19:54,710
出海之前要找到所有的细节
Find out every detail\nbefore you set sail.

213
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:56,720
哦 出海 我也想
Oh, set sail. Love to.

214
00:19:56,860 --> 00:19:59,090
但那样 我可得要条船
But for that, I may need a ship.

215
00:19:59,230 --> 00:20:02,530
那边那些伙计 他们有船
Those folk, over there,\nthey have a ship.

216
00:20:02,660 --> 00:20:05,220
他们正招人呢
They're signing up sailors right now.

217
00:20:05,370 --> 00:20:07,560
{\fnarial black\fs14\4a&H64&\fscx90\fscy110}My heart is pierced by Cupid

218
00:20:07,700 --> 00:20:09,690
{\fnarial black\fs14\4a&H64&\fscx90\fscy110}I disdain all glittering gold

219
00:20:09,840 --> 00:20:12,200
最后一件事 小杰
And one last thing, Jackie.

220
00:20:13,540 --> 00:20:16,910
泉会考验你\n记住我的话
The Fountain will test you.\nMark my words.

221
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:18,380
{\fnarial black\fs14\4a&H64&\fscx90\fscy110}My heart is pierced by Cupid

222
00:20:18,510 --> 00:20:20,450
{\fnarial black\fs14\4a&H64&\fscx90\fscy110}I disdain all glittering gold

223
00:20:20,580 --> 00:20:23,310
{\fnarial black\fs14\4a&H64&\fscx90\fscy110}There is nothing can console me

224
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:26,080
{\fnarial black\fs14\4a&H64&\fscx90\fscy110}But my jolly sailor bold

225
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:41,430
我听说你们正在招人
I hear you be recruiting a crew.

226
00:20:41,570 --> 00:20:43,630
是啊 那是
Aye. That is,

227
00:20:43,770 --> 00:20:47,570
杰克・斯派洛要准备远行
Jack Sparrow be putting together\na modest venture.

228
00:20:49,310 --> 00:20:51,640
你挺有胆的啊 是不?
You got some nerve, ain't ya?

229
00:20:51,780 --> 00:20:53,300
那么高调的穿成那样?
Turning up here dressed like that?

230
00:20:53,450 --> 00:20:55,440
你是什么 什么冒牌货么?
What are you, some kind of impostor?

231
00:20:55,580 --> 00:20:57,780
你知道我是谁么 哥们?
Have you any idea who I am, mate?

232
00:21:00,190 --> 00:21:01,590
嘿 伙计们!
Oi, muckers!

233
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:04,320
这儿有个小子忘记自己的名字了!
There's a bloke here what's\nforgotten his own name!

234
00:21:07,130 --> 00:21:09,360
小伙子们 我和斯派洛一起出航
Lads, I'm sailing with Sparrow.

235
00:21:09,530 --> 00:21:11,290
谁要给水手买杯酒?
Who'll buy a sailor a drink?

236
00:21:13,900 --> 00:21:14,920
谁是下一个?
Who's next?

237
00:21:23,340 --> 00:21:26,440
多给我们带点这样的
Bring us some more of those ones.

238
00:21:26,580 --> 00:21:28,780
是啊 做四个吧
Yeah, make it four.

239
00:21:37,260 --> 00:21:41,350
你偷了我的身份\n我是来揭穿你的
You've stolen me,\nand I'm here to take meself back.

240
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,160
别再做那个动作了
Stop doing that.

241
00:23:48,420 --> 00:23:51,120
只有一个活着的人知道那招
Only one person alive knows that move.

242
00:23:58,930 --> 00:24:00,990
早就想做这个了
Always wanted to do that.

243
00:24:02,100 --> 00:24:03,730
你好啊 安洁莉卡
Hello, Angelica.

244
00:24:06,110 --> 00:24:10,010
你好 杰克 大开眼界了没
Hello, Jack. Are you impressed?

245
00:24:10,140 --> 00:24:13,340
我想我差点有一次或者两次\n可以杀了你
I think I almost killed you\nonce or twice there.

246
00:24:13,480 --> 00:24:17,540
我真感动 这是最真诚的恭维了
I'm touched at this most\nsincerest form of flattery.

247
00:24:18,990 --> 00:24:21,220
但为什么?
But why?

248
00:24:21,390 --> 00:24:24,020
你是唯一我能冒充的海盗
You were the only pirate\nI thought I would pass for.

249
00:24:24,160 --> 00:24:25,890
这可不是恭维
That is not a compliment.

250
00:24:28,330 --> 00:24:31,990
别担心 杰克\n我很早前就原谅你了
Don't worry, Jack.\nI forgave you a long time ago.

251
00:24:32,130 --> 00:24:37,300
- 为什么? 离开你么?\n- 记清楚是我离开你的
- For what? For leaving you?\n- Recall that I left you.

252
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:41,340
一个绅士会允许小姐活在她杜撰的世界
A gentleman allows a lady\nto maintain her fictions.

253
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:45,000
你看 斯派洛 只要我的水手们拿到钱
Look, Sparrow. As long as\nmy sailors get their money,

254
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:49,170
他们会愿意忍受任何的怪癖
they're willing to put up with\nany number of peculiarities.

255
00:24:49,320 --> 00:24:53,010
有一件事我不永远会忍受
There is one peculiarity\nwith which I will not put up with.

256
00:24:53,650 --> 00:24:56,710
要冒充我 就要冒充成船长
I will be impersonated as "Captain."\nNothing less.

257
00:24:56,860 --> 00:24:58,880
呃 那样的话 你需要艘船
Well, for that, you need a ship,

258
00:24:59,030 --> 00:25:01,520
恰好呢 我有一艘
and as it turns out, I have one.

259
00:25:02,460 --> 00:25:04,400
我是需要船
I could use a ship.

260
00:25:04,530 --> 00:25:07,260
我听说你去过不老泉
I hear tell you've been to the Fountain.

261
00:25:07,430 --> 00:25:09,560
最近有好多的道听途说啊
There be a lot of hear-telling\ngoing on these days.

262
00:25:09,700 --> 00:25:14,230
- 不老泉\n- 最亲爱的安洁莉卡 不用怕
- The Fountain of Youth.\n- Dearest Angelica, fret not.

263
00:25:14,370 --> 00:25:17,140
你还有几年不错的光阴呢
You still have a few usable years left.

264
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:20,610
总是那么会说话
Always so charming.

265
00:25:20,780 --> 00:25:21,870
你没回答我
You didn't answer me.

266
00:25:22,020 --> 00:25:24,580
好 且不管那泉\n浪费时间 真的...
Aye. Regarding the Fountain.\nWaste of time, really...

267
00:25:24,720 --> 00:25:28,350
夫人 我发现一个不像海员的人\n在到处打探消息
Milady, I see unseamanlike fellows\nof an officious-looking nature.

268
00:25:28,490 --> 00:25:31,150
无耻的海盗!\n找到他们! 
Wretched pirates!\nFind 'em! Maggots!

269
00:25:35,360 --> 00:25:36,520
你的朋友?
Friends of yours?

270
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:39,290
我可能是无心的\n得罪了国王或是别的谁
I may have unintentionally\nslighted some king or other.

271
00:25:39,470 --> 00:25:41,230
开门!
Open it!

272
00:25:41,370 --> 00:25:44,030
- 是啊 你一点都没变\n- 是说我要改变吗?
- Yeah, you haven't changed.\n- Implying the need?

273
00:25:44,170 --> 00:25:45,540
是
Yes.

274
00:25:45,670 --> 00:25:47,370
开门 以陛下的名义
Open this door,\nin the name of His Majesty.

275
00:25:47,510 --> 00:25:50,870
你背叛了的\n你勾引我还利用了我
You betrayed me.\nYou seduced me and you used me.

276
00:25:51,010 --> 00:25:52,740
我当初对男人的花招都知之甚少
I was innocent of the ways of men.

277
00:25:52,880 --> 00:25:56,180
你对付我这情场老手 也花招也不少
You demonstrated a lot of technique\nfor someone I supposedly corrupted.

278
00:25:56,280 --> 00:25:59,080
快逃啊 这里 快 夫人!
Imminent danger. Here, now, milady!

279
00:25:59,220 --> 00:26:00,850
打开!
Open it!

280
00:26:00,990 --> 00:26:04,550
我都准备好我的誓言了 可你...
I was ready to take my vows. And you...

281
00:26:04,690 --> 00:26:07,320
你跑去西班牙修院做什么?
What were you doing in\na Spanish convent, anyway?

282
00:26:07,490 --> 00:26:10,220
我搞错了 以为是妓院
Mistook it for a brothel.\nHonest mistake.

283
00:26:14,170 --> 00:26:15,790
- 他在那儿!\n- 就在上面!
- There he is!\n- Over there!

284
00:26:34,220 --> 00:26:36,150
我们现在不占优势
We are at a disadvantage.

285
00:26:36,290 --> 00:26:39,690
说你自己吧\n被你冒充的人可不觉得
Speak for yourself.\nUnlike some who pretend to be,

286
00:26:39,860 --> 00:26:41,620
但事实上 你连蜡烛都拿不稳
but cannot, in fact, hold a candle to,

287
00:26:41,760 --> 00:26:43,230
我才是杰克・斯派洛船长
I am Captain Jack Sparrow.

288
00:27:20,430 --> 00:27:22,990
你怎么能说我利用你?
How can you say I used you?

289
00:27:23,140 --> 00:27:25,330
你自己心里清楚
You know exactly how.

290
00:27:25,470 --> 00:27:28,600
我知道 但你怎么能那么说?
I know, but how can you say it?

291
00:27:33,250 --> 00:27:36,740
- 怎么样\n- 什么怎么样
- So, what is it?\n- What is what?

292
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:38,410
不老泉啊
About the Fountain.

293
00:27:41,020 --> 00:27:42,050
你知道多少
What do you know?

294
00:27:44,020 --> 00:27:45,620
你不会恰好拿着
You don't happen to be in possession

295
00:27:45,730 --> 00:27:48,990
两只庞德・里昂的银圣杯吧?
of two silver chalices,
circa Ponce de Len?

296
00:27:49,700 --> 00:27:51,560
- 没有\n- 哈 我就知道
- No.\n- Thought not.

297
00:27:51,700 --> 00:27:55,330
- 怎么了?\n- 我听到一些故事
- Why?\n- I hear stories.

298
00:27:55,470 --> 00:27:57,300
谣言
Rumors.

299
00:27:57,400 --> 00:27:59,570
你当然知道有仪式
You are, of course, aware of the ritual.

300
00:28:00,540 --> 00:28:01,630
嗯 我知道
Yes, I am.

301
00:28:03,980 --> 00:28:06,710
是什么?\n需要带什么去呢?
What is it?\nWhat is required?

302
00:28:11,320 --> 00:28:13,310
一条美人鱼 杰克
A mermaid, Jack.

303
00:28:21,290 --> 00:28:22,690
这绝对是个错误
There's been a mistake.

304
00:28:22,830 --> 00:28:26,360
是无期徒刑 不是死刑 我不能死!
It's a life sentence, not death. Life!

305
00:28:31,770 --> 00:28:35,100
- 巴博萨\n- 谢谢 绅士们
- Barbossa.\n- Thank you, gentlemen.

306
00:28:35,240 --> 00:28:38,230
我相信你会打套索吧
I trust you can tie a noose.

307
00:28:38,380 --> 00:28:39,780
那挺难的
That's a hard thing,

308
00:28:39,910 --> 00:28:42,910
逼人给圈自己的上吊绳
forcing a man to twist\nhis own hanging rope.

309
00:28:43,750 --> 00:28:46,580
自己种下的恶果得自己尝
You must lie in your bed\nthe way you made it.

310
00:28:48,420 --> 00:28:49,790
你是怎么了?
What's happened to you?

311
00:28:49,920 --> 00:28:53,360
- 杰克・斯派洛在哪儿?\n- 他逃了
- Where be Jack Sparrow?\n- He escaped.

312
00:28:53,460 --> 00:28:54,930
我时间表很紧 吉布斯
I'm on a tight schedule, Gibbs.

313
00:28:55,060 --> 00:28:57,430
皇家探宝舰队天一亮就要起航了
The HMS Providence\nsets sail at first light.

314
00:28:57,560 --> 00:28:59,730
如果你不想看它出发\n就吊死在这儿
If you do not care to watch it\nhanging here dead,

315
00:28:59,870 --> 00:29:01,890
搞得满嘴的苍蝇...
with a mouth full of flies...

316
00:29:03,540 --> 00:29:05,160
否则...现在就交代
...speak now.

317
00:29:06,910 --> 00:29:09,400
带我跟你走吧\n任何地方...
Take me with you.\nAny point of the compass...

318
00:29:09,540 --> 00:29:14,380
带你去哪儿 吉布斯\n不老泉? 嗯?
Take you where, Gibbs?\nThe Fountain? Aye?

319
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:17,510
那是杰克打算去的地方?
Is that where Jack be headed?

320
00:29:17,680 --> 00:29:21,710
你有什么能告诉我的 吉布斯?
Have you anything\nyou can offer me, Gibbs?

321
00:29:21,820 --> 00:29:23,380
随便什么啊
Anything at all?

322
00:29:25,160 --> 00:29:28,650
我明着跟你说吧\n你别想看见黎明了
Upon me naked word,\nyou'll not see the dawn.

323
00:29:36,700 --> 00:29:38,430
交过来
Hand it over.

324
00:29:43,180 --> 00:29:45,470
- 你这蠢人\n- 我有足够的时间
- You fool!\n- I had just enough time

325
00:29:45,610 --> 00:29:48,100
来学习这些阴间的圆圈
to study those infernal circles.

326
00:29:48,250 --> 00:29:52,880
每条路线 每个目的地\n都存在...这里
Every route, every destination.\nAll safe... in here.

327
00:29:54,390 --> 00:29:58,410
欢迎回归皇家海军\n吉布斯先生
Welcome back to His Majesty's navy,\nMaster Gibbs.

328
00:30:11,500 --> 00:30:13,500
准备起航 水手
Show a leg, sailor!

329
00:30:13,640 --> 00:30:14,870
遵命 先生
Aye, sir.

330
00:30:16,410 --> 00:30:17,710
什么?
What?

331
00:30:17,840 --> 00:30:21,040
- 这误会大了\n- 继续走
- There's been a horrible mistake.\n- Keep moving.

332
00:30:22,550 --> 00:30:25,520
- 我不该在这里\n- 很多人在海里醒来
- I'm not supposed to be here.\n- Many a man's woken up at sea,

333
00:30:25,650 --> 00:30:27,590
茫茫然不知是怎么回事
no idea what, when, wherefore or why.

334
00:30:27,750 --> 00:30:29,980
完全忘记前晚签下合同
No memory of the night afore,\nwhence he signed up

335
00:30:30,120 --> 00:30:31,650
然后把所有的意外之财全部拿去买醉
and drank away all his bonus money.

336
00:30:31,790 --> 00:30:33,780
不 不 不 你不明白 伙计
No, no, no. You don't understand, mate.

337
00:30:33,890 --> 00:30:36,330
我是杰克・斯派洛船长\n独一无二的
I'm Captain Jack Sparrow.\nThe original. The only.

338
00:30:36,460 --> 00:30:39,020
我是斯克罗姆 幸会 现在继续走
Scrum, and the pleasure's all mine.\nNow, keep moving.

339
00:30:47,540 --> 00:30:49,010
斯克罗姆
Scrum.

340
00:30:49,140 --> 00:30:51,370
把你的胳膊肘收回去
Get your elbows in!

341
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:55,750
为什么有一具玻璃棺材
Why is there a glass coffin?

342
00:30:55,880 --> 00:30:58,350
我看起来像管事的吗
Do I look like a man in charge?

343
00:30:58,480 --> 00:31:01,420
- 我在哪里\n- 抱歉 斯派洛船长先生
- Where am I?\n- 'Scuse me, Captain Sparrow, sir.

344
00:31:01,550 --> 00:31:03,220
十分荣幸地欢迎您
I be right honored\nto welcome you aboard

345
00:31:03,360 --> 00:31:06,620
登上臭名昭著的安妮女王复仇号
our world-renowned vessel of infamy,\nQueen Anne's Revenge.

346
00:31:10,030 --> 00:31:11,690
黑胡子的船
Blackbeard.

347
00:31:28,050 --> 00:31:29,910
干活
Work!

348
00:31:33,720 --> 00:31:37,450
- 他长得很奇怪\n- 他是僵尸人
- He's a curious one.\n- He's been zombiefied.

349
00:31:38,730 --> 00:31:40,250
僵尸人
Zombiefied.

350
00:31:40,390 --> 00:31:43,890
黑胡子船长干的\n所有带头的都是
Blackbeard's doing.\nAll the officers are the same.

351
00:31:44,030 --> 00:31:45,760
这样他们才更顺从
Makes 'em more compliant.

352
00:31:47,030 --> 00:31:49,000
脾气暴躁嘛
And perpetually ill-tempered.

353
00:31:50,700 --> 00:31:53,300
- 快点吧 用力擦\n- 嗯
- Come on. Scrub.\n- Yeah.

354
00:32:00,380 --> 00:32:04,010
拉 拉 拉
Pull! Pull! Pull!

355
00:32:08,550 --> 00:32:11,110
航行了五天 至少
Five days underway, at least.

356
00:32:11,260 --> 00:32:15,090
对 你闻着海水的味就知道吗
Aye. You can tell that\nby the smell of the sea?

357
00:32:15,230 --> 00:32:16,960
是船员的臭味
Smell of the crew.

358
00:32:20,530 --> 00:32:23,630
喂 那个倒霉蛋做了什么
Oi. What did that poor sod do?

359
00:32:23,770 --> 00:32:25,800
我最好不要重蹈覆辙
And how can I make sure to not?

360
00:32:25,940 --> 00:32:28,270
他吗? 他是个基督徒
Him? Churchly fellow.

361
00:32:28,410 --> 00:32:30,430
总是念叨着万能的主啊
Always going on about the Lord Almighty.

362
00:32:30,580 --> 00:32:32,310
是船上的狂热教徒?
Bible-thumper on this ship?

363
00:32:32,450 --> 00:32:34,350
他以前是传教士
A missionary is his story.

364
00:32:34,480 --> 00:32:37,240
我听说他在一次掠夺中被俘
What I heard was\nhe got captured in a raid.

365
00:32:37,350 --> 00:32:40,250
船上其余人都被杀了\n不过他没有
Rest of the ship got killed,\nbut not 'im.

366
00:32:40,350 --> 00:32:41,680
大副不让杀他
First mate wouldn't let it happen

367
00:32:41,820 --> 00:32:44,520
因为他之前是信主的
on account of his premier standing\nwith the Lord.

368
00:32:44,660 --> 00:32:49,060
大副拼上她的性命帮一个囚犯
A first mate sticking her neck out\nfor some prisoner.

369
00:32:49,230 --> 00:32:50,820
实在是太少见了
That you don't see.

370
00:32:50,960 --> 00:32:53,660
"她" 大副是个女的?
"Her"? First mate is a "her"?

371
00:32:53,800 --> 00:32:55,030
回去工作
Back to work!

372
00:33:04,340 --> 00:33:06,610
平稳向前
Steady as she goes.

373
00:33:20,830 --> 00:33:25,200
你是个冷酷 没有感情 难缠的坏女人
You are a ruthless,\nsoulless, cross-grained cur.

374
00:33:25,330 --> 00:33:28,820
- 我告诉过你我有船\n- 不 是黑胡子有船
- I told you I had a ship.\n- No, Blackbeard has a ship,

375
00:33:28,970 --> 00:33:31,770
现在我成了上面的囚犯
upon which I am now imprisoned.

376
00:33:31,940 --> 00:33:33,910
我们做得到的 杰克
We can do this, Jack.

377
00:33:34,040 --> 00:33:38,640
不老泉 你一直想找到的
The Fountain of Youth,\nlike you always wanted.

378
00:33:38,750 --> 00:33:43,880
黑胡子 爱德华・汀奇\n让所有海盗闻风丧胆的海盗
Blackbeard. Edward Teach.\nThe pirate all pirates fear.

379
00:33:44,020 --> 00:33:46,180
闲着没事时让死人复活
Resurrector of the dead\nin his spare time.

380
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:49,190
- 他会听我的\n- 他谁的都不听
- He will listen to me.\n- He listens to no one.

381
00:33:49,320 --> 00:33:52,220
或许他听自己亲生女儿的呢?
Maybe to his own daughter?

382
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:57,700
女儿...他亲生女儿
Daughter as in... beget by?

383
00:33:58,560 --> 00:34:02,400
失散了很久 最近才相认
Long-lost. Recently found.

384
00:34:02,540 --> 00:34:06,370
她全身心爱着她亲爱的爸爸
Who loves her dear papa\nwith all her soul.

385
00:34:06,510 --> 00:34:08,570
- 他相信?\n- 我说服了他
- He bought that?\n- I sold that.

386
00:34:16,020 --> 00:34:17,810
然后他是为他自己找不老泉
Then it's the Fountain of Youth for him,

387
00:34:17,980 --> 00:34:20,820
或者是为他和你 不是为你和我吧
or him and you, not you and me.

388
00:34:20,990 --> 00:34:23,050
没错 杰克 最精彩的是
No, Jack, that's the best part.

389
00:34:23,190 --> 00:34:25,250
他即将死去
He will be dead.

390
00:34:26,560 --> 00:34:28,960
你要亲手杀了他?
You'll be handling\nthat part yourself, then?

391
00:34:29,100 --> 00:34:31,360
有一个预言
There is a prophecy.

392
00:34:31,460 --> 00:34:33,690
也许你不相信超自然现象
Maybe you don't believe\nin the supernatural.

393
00:34:33,800 --> 00:34:36,290
哦 不 我见过一两次这样的事
Oh, no, no.\nI've seen a thing or two.

394
00:34:38,870 --> 00:34:42,830
预言是这么说的
The prophecy is this:

395
00:34:43,010 --> 00:34:46,810
黑胡子在两周内就会死
Blackbeard will meet his death\nwithin a fortnight

396
00:34:46,950 --> 00:34:50,400
死在一个独脚人的手上
at the hands of a one-legged man.

397
00:34:50,550 --> 00:34:52,750
所以他才不是想要不老泉 杰克
That's why he needs the Fountain, Jack.

398
00:35:09,070 --> 00:35:11,830
吉布斯先生 我们没有地图
Master Gibbs, short we are a map.

399
00:35:11,970 --> 00:35:15,070
也许你能好心给我们指个方向
Perhaps you'd be so kind\nas to provide us an heading.

400
00:35:18,850 --> 00:35:20,940
做点好事 给我倒杯酒
Be a gem and pour me a gulper.

401
00:35:21,080 --> 00:35:24,520
我们是私掠船 不是海盗 吉布斯先生
Nay. We be privateers,\nnot pirates, Master Gibbs.

402
00:35:24,650 --> 00:35:26,780
我们以国王的名义做事
And in the king's name,\nwe behave as such.

403
00:35:26,920 --> 00:35:29,750
遵命 船长
Aye, Captain.

404
00:35:33,160 --> 00:35:35,960
我们在正确的航线上吗 吉布斯?
Be we on the proper course, Gibbs?

405
00:35:36,100 --> 00:35:40,690
是的 航线正确 这就是证据
Aye, it be proper. There's your proof.

406
00:35:47,210 --> 00:35:48,500
西班牙人
The Spaniard.

407
00:35:50,080 --> 00:35:54,810
全体船员 进入备战状态\n驶向迎风面
All hands! Battle stations!\nGet to windward!

408
00:35:54,950 --> 00:35:58,010
- 全体船员 迎风\n- 准备开炮
- All hands, windward!\n- Harden up two points!

409
00:35:58,150 --> 00:36:01,590
- 准备开炮\n- 大炮就位
- Two points!\n- Cast loose the cannons!

410
00:36:05,560 --> 00:36:09,320
- 炮手各就各位\n- 就位 炮手准备就绪 先生
- Gunners, take posts!\n- Take position! Gunners ready, sir!

411
00:36:09,460 --> 00:36:13,330
- 出! 推!\n- 等我命令
- Out! Thrust!\n- Await orders.

412
00:36:15,430 --> 00:36:16,800
稳住
Steady!

413
00:36:18,140 --> 00:36:19,730
炮弹装好 等待命令 先生
Guns armed, awaiting orders, sir.

414
00:36:25,510 --> 00:36:29,070
先生 下令啊 先生!
Sir. Orders, sir?

415
00:36:35,690 --> 00:36:38,420
他连头都不转过来
He never so much as turned his head.

416
00:36:38,560 --> 00:36:40,420
不老泉才是目标
The Fountain is the prize.

417
00:36:40,560 --> 00:36:44,190
甚至都不愿浪费时间来击沉我们
It appears we be not even worth\nthe time it'd take to sink us.

418
00:36:44,330 --> 00:36:48,230
现在我们落后了 全体船员 升帆
And now we've fallen behind.\nAll hands, make more sail!

419
00:36:48,370 --> 00:36:50,930
全体船员 升帆
All hands, more sail!

420
00:36:51,070 --> 00:36:54,400
全速前进
Ride hard between wind and tide!

421
00:37:04,380 --> 00:37:07,980
先生们 我要说的是暴动
The topic, gentlemen, is mutiny.

422
00:37:08,750 --> 00:37:10,550
最恐怖的暴动
Mutiny most foul.

423
00:37:10,690 --> 00:37:14,220
是的 我是要来当杰克・斯派洛的水手\n不是冒牌货
Aye. I signed up to sail\nunder Jack Sparrow, not some pretender.

424
00:37:14,360 --> 00:37:15,620
还是个女人
And a lady, at that.

425
00:37:15,760 --> 00:37:17,960
也没提到有可怕的僵尸人
And mention was failed to\nbe made of this uncanny crew.

426
00:37:18,100 --> 00:37:20,460
我怕得腿都软了
Make my toes curl, they do.

427
00:37:20,600 --> 00:37:23,660
我拿到了 全部
I got 'em. All of them.

428
00:37:23,840 --> 00:37:25,770
- 干得好\n- 好样的
- Well done.\n- Good lad.

429
00:37:25,910 --> 00:37:28,340
那么我说 黑胡子船长
On to it, then. Blackbeard.

430
00:37:28,510 --> 00:37:30,940
- 他有什么习惯\n- 他几乎都待在船长室
- What are his habits?\n- Stays mostly to his cabin.

431
00:37:31,080 --> 00:37:33,880
没错 差不多都待在船长室
That's right, mostly to his cabin.

432
00:37:33,980 --> 00:37:37,210
- 好 不过当他出来时...\n- 他根本不出来
- Yes, but when he comes out...\n- He don't really come out.

433
00:37:39,190 --> 00:37:40,550
他一定有出来的时候
He must come out sometime.

434
00:37:41,420 --> 00:37:43,620
没有
Not really, no.

435
00:37:45,460 --> 00:37:47,150
你们谁曾和他一起出过海吗
Any of you sail with him before?

436
00:37:47,290 --> 00:37:48,760
- 不 没有\n- 我从来没有过
- No, no.\n- I've never.

437
00:37:48,890 --> 00:37:49,920
完全没有
Definitely not.

438
00:37:50,060 --> 00:37:53,930
- 你们有人见过他吗\n- 没有
- Any of you seen him before?\n- Not really, no.

439
00:37:55,530 --> 00:37:57,700
只待在船长室 没人和他出过海
Stays to his cabin,\nno one sailed with him,

440
00:37:57,870 --> 00:37:59,900
没人见过他
no one's seen him...

441
00:38:00,070 --> 00:38:03,040
好消息 先生们 这艘不是黑胡子的船
Good news, gentlemen.\nThis is not Blackbeard's ship.

442
00:38:03,210 --> 00:38:05,010
这不是安妮女王复仇号
This is not the Queen Anne's Revenge.

443
00:38:05,140 --> 00:38:07,170
不 这绝对是安妮女王复仇号
No, this be the Queen Anne's Revenge,\nright enough.

444
00:38:07,310 --> 00:38:08,780
你怎么知道
How do you know?

445
00:38:08,910 --> 00:38:12,180
我看到了船的名字 在船后面
I've seen the name,\non the back of the ship.

446
00:38:15,420 --> 00:38:20,380
先生们 大伙儿们
Gentlemen, sirs, fellow conscriptees...

447
00:38:22,130 --> 00:38:24,260
你们被骗了
...you have been monstrously deceived.

448
00:38:24,360 --> 00:38:28,530
- 我们被耍了吗\n- 是的
- We are decepted, then?\n- Yes.

449
00:38:28,670 --> 00:38:31,600
你们都不知道此行的目的
You've nay been informed\nof a destination.

450
00:38:31,700 --> 00:38:33,870
死亡就在我们眼前
Death lies before us

451
00:38:34,010 --> 00:38:38,840
当我们找到不老泉时
as we sail for the Fountain of Youth.

452
00:38:40,650 --> 00:38:42,340
我们处境不妙啊 伙计们
It would be a sorry plight, mates.

453
00:38:42,480 --> 00:38:46,610
- 死亡 确确实实?\n- 黯淡灵魂的花园
- Death, for certain.\n- The garden of darkened souls.

454
00:38:46,720 --> 00:38:50,090
- 我们的生命将过早结束\n- 除非...
- Untimely our ends will be.\n- Unless...

455
00:38:50,260 --> 00:38:52,750
我们夺下这艘船
...we take the ship.

456
00:38:54,060 --> 00:38:57,620
那我们就夺下这船 就现在
We take the ship, then. Now!

457
00:39:01,830 --> 00:39:03,360
行动吧
Go on, then.

458
00:39:04,140 --> 00:39:06,760
- 帮我 伙伴\n- 把它给我
- Help me, shipmates!\n- Give it to 'em!

459
00:39:06,940 --> 00:39:09,170
- 醒醒 这是我们的\n- 快
- Wake up! It's ours!\n- Come on!

460
00:39:09,310 --> 00:39:10,970
起来 给我挪开
Get up! Off your backside!

461
00:39:12,510 --> 00:39:14,880
- 你给我起来\n- 把武器给他们 
- Get off your fannies!\n- Take it to them, lads!

462
00:39:15,010 --> 00:39:16,850
快帮着我 打啊
Help me! Fight!

463
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:31,800
杰克
Jack.

464
00:39:33,430 --> 00:39:38,060
如果这是个梦\n你可以留着剑和靴子
If this is a dream,\nyou can keep the sword and boots on.

465
00:39:40,210 --> 00:39:42,730
- 如果不是...\n- 这是个梦
- If it's not...\n- It's a dream.

466
00:39:48,350 --> 00:39:49,410
不 这不是梦
No, it's not!

467
00:39:50,720 --> 00:39:53,280
我认为我应该好心给你个警告\n我们在夺船
I thought I should give you\nfair warning, we're taking the ship.

468
00:39:54,320 --> 00:39:55,810
不是针对你个人
Nothing personal.

469
00:39:56,890 --> 00:39:58,790
如果你别插手
Think you might be better off\nif you just...

470
00:40:00,430 --> 00:40:01,760
会比较好
...stay out of it.

471
00:40:25,350 --> 00:40:26,650
碍事
Boggit.

472
00:40:48,140 --> 00:40:49,540
混蛋
Wretch!

473
00:41:19,170 --> 00:41:21,160
你要么加入我们 要么就是敌人
You're either with us or against us!

474
00:41:21,310 --> 00:41:23,500
我不加入 也不是敌人
I am not with you,\nneither am I against you!

475
00:41:23,640 --> 00:41:25,010
他这样可以?
Can he do that?

476
00:41:25,140 --> 00:41:28,170
他是教徒 我想他必须这样
He's religious.\nI believe it's required.

477
00:41:33,490 --> 00:41:36,820
奋战到底吧 你们这些蠢猴子
Fight to the bitter end,\nyou cack-handed deck apes!

478
00:41:48,630 --> 00:41:51,030
抓住他 把他绑起来
Take him, men.\nTie him down tight!

479
00:42:05,780 --> 00:42:07,510
船是我们的了
The ship is ours!

480
00:42:36,350 --> 00:42:38,580
先生们
Gentlemen.

481
00:42:46,030 --> 00:42:49,520
我不明白了
I be placed in a bewilderment.

482
00:42:49,630 --> 00:42:54,290
我在里面休息
There I were, resting,

483
00:42:54,430 --> 00:42:59,100
突然间 我听到甲板上的吵闹声
and upon a sudden,\nI hear an ungodly row on deck.

484
00:43:02,170 --> 00:43:04,110
水手放下手中的活
Sailors abandon their posts

485
00:43:04,240 --> 00:43:06,770
未经同意 擅离职守
without orders, without leave.

486
00:43:07,880 --> 00:43:11,110
船桅前的那些人
Men before the mast,

487
00:43:11,250 --> 00:43:13,650
就想要把船据为己有
taking the ship for themselves.

488
00:43:15,390 --> 00:43:17,690
这算什么啊 大副
What be that, First Mate?

489
00:43:17,860 --> 00:43:20,690
- 暴动 船长\n- 再说一次?
- Mutiny, Captain.\n- Again?

490
00:43:20,860 --> 00:43:23,830
- 暴动\n- 听到了
- Mutiny!\n- Aye.

491
00:43:24,400 --> 00:43:26,090
暴动
Mutiny.

492
00:43:28,600 --> 00:43:32,040
暴动的下场是什么?
And what fate befalls mutineers?

493
00:43:32,200 --> 00:43:35,700
大家知道答案的 是吗
Now, we know the answer to that,\ndo we not?

494
00:43:35,870 --> 00:43:39,440
暴动者会被吊死
Mutineers hang!

495
00:44:29,260 --> 00:44:30,990
船长 我想报告有人暴动
Captain, I wish to report a mutiny.

496
00:44:32,500 --> 00:44:34,090
我可以指出是哪些人干的
I can name fingers and point names.

497
00:44:34,270 --> 00:44:35,730
不需要了 斯派洛先生
No need, Mr. Sparrow.

498
00:44:35,870 --> 00:44:39,100
他们都是小绵羊\n而你 他们的主脑
They are sheep. You, their shepherd.

499
00:44:44,010 --> 00:44:46,710
我有没有说过 先生\n您的女儿有多可爱?
Have I mentioned, sir,\nwhat a lovely daughter you have?

500
00:44:47,350 --> 00:44:49,780
垂死前的灵魂最后的美景
A fitting last sight for a doomed soul.

501
00:44:49,950 --> 00:44:52,350
别忘了 父亲 我们需要他
Remember, Father.\nWe need him.

502
00:44:52,480 --> 00:44:53,970
如果我不时不时的杀个人
If I don't kill a man\nevery now and then,

503
00:44:54,090 --> 00:44:56,520
- 他们就会忘了我是谁\n- 懦夫
- they forget who I am.\n- Coward!

504
00:44:58,160 --> 00:45:00,390
他们没有忘记
They do not forget.

505
00:45:00,490 --> 00:45:02,860
你的船员认清你是个卑鄙小人
Your crew sees you\nfor the miscreant you are.

506
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:05,330
懦夫 不管你杀多少人
A coward, no matter how many you slay.

507
00:45:05,430 --> 00:45:07,870
今天第二次了啊 我又糊涂了
Twice in one day,\nI find myself in a bewilderment.

508
00:45:08,000 --> 00:45:10,130
你不是糊涂 是害怕
You are not bewildered, you are afraid.

509
00:45:10,840 --> 00:45:13,130
你不敢走向正义光明之路
You dare not walk the path of\nrighteousness, the way of the light.

510
00:45:13,310 --> 00:45:17,540
不是的 先生 情况其实很简单
No, sir. The truth is\nit be much simpler than all that.

511
00:45:17,680 --> 00:45:20,580
- 我就是个大坏蛋\n- 这也对
- I am a bad man.\n- That, too.

512
00:45:20,710 --> 00:45:22,700
我也许也得杀你 传道士
I might have to kill you too, catechist.

513
00:45:22,850 --> 00:45:25,440
- 不!\n- 跟她的拉丁妈妈一样强悍啊
- No!\n- All Latin blood like her mother.

514
00:45:25,580 --> 00:45:27,680
爸爸 我求你
Father, I beg you.

515
00:45:27,790 --> 00:45:31,550
我老忘了为何有个传教士在船上
There I be again,\nforgetting why the missionary is here.

516
00:45:31,690 --> 00:45:36,090
我女儿想拯救我的灵魂\n或者是仅剩下的灵魂
My daughter fears for my soul,\nor what's left of it.

517
00:45:37,100 --> 00:45:40,760
你真的想拯救我吗 孩子?
You truly wish to save me, my child?

518
00:45:40,900 --> 00:45:42,830
每个灵魂都能被救赎
Every soul can be saved.

519
00:45:43,900 --> 00:45:45,770
真的吗 年轻的传道士?
Be that true, young cleric?

520
00:45:45,900 --> 00:45:49,600
是的  不过 你估计希望不大啊
Yes. Though you I see\nas a bit of a long shot.

521
00:45:50,610 --> 00:45:54,570
但我仍为在这个地狱般得船上的\n每个不幸的船员祷告
Still, I pray for every unfortunate soul\non this hell-bound vessel.

522
00:45:57,120 --> 00:45:59,780
你能用你的信仰解除我的武装
You disarm me with your faith.

523
00:46:01,150 --> 00:46:02,620
8声钟响!
Eight bells!

524
00:46:02,760 --> 00:46:05,750
哪一个不幸的人在守了望台的啊
Which of you unfortunate souls\nstood watch?

525
00:46:05,890 --> 00:46:10,850
- 我 是我在守望\n- 炮手
- I did. I stood watch.\n- Gunner.

526
00:46:16,240 --> 00:46:17,630
你吗?
You?

527
00:46:18,300 --> 00:46:19,930
是
Aye.

528
00:46:20,470 --> 00:46:22,270
是哦
Aye.

529
00:46:22,410 --> 00:46:24,400
厨子
The cook.

530
00:46:24,510 --> 00:46:27,410
很好 把长船放下去!
Perfect. Lower the longboat!

531
00:46:32,650 --> 00:46:34,640
放他过去!
Bring her about!

532
00:46:46,200 --> 00:46:49,220
- 你干嘛要这样?\n- 暴动的刑罚 法律解释得很清楚
- Why do you do this?\n- Mutiny. Our laws be clear.

533
00:46:49,400 --> 00:46:51,670
船长也能依法开恩的啊
Our laws allow the Captain\nto show leniency.

534
00:46:51,800 --> 00:46:54,430
我给过这个人机会决定命运
I have given this man\na chance to determine his fate,

535
00:46:54,540 --> 00:46:56,240
不是每个人都有这样的机会
a gift not afforded to all.

536
00:47:05,350 --> 00:47:06,820
该你了
Oh, you now.

537
00:47:08,120 --> 00:47:10,710
给你个机会证明祈祷的作用
Chance to show the worth\nof your prayers.

538
00:47:10,860 --> 00:47:14,920
祈祷他脱离...邪恶?
Pray he be delivered from... evil?

539
00:47:23,240 --> 00:47:24,600
定下航向!
Course made!

540
00:47:24,770 --> 00:47:26,600
停 给他一个机会\n给你自己...
Stop. Give that man a chance.\nGive yourself a...

541
00:47:52,330 --> 00:47:54,930
我觉得我最接近造物主是什么时候吗?
You know when I feel closest\nto our Maker?

542
00:47:55,070 --> 00:47:56,930
是当我看到苦难 痛苦和绝望的时候
When I see suffering, pain and anguish.

543
00:47:57,070 --> 00:47:59,590
这时他真正的愿望才会显现
That's when the true design\nof this world is revealed.

544
00:47:59,740 --> 00:48:03,440
在苦难和悲剧出现时 他才会显现出来 
And I see it revealed when in times\nof hardship and tragedy,

545
00:48:03,580 --> 00:48:05,870
他才会那些需要人恩施
kindness and compassion\nare shown to those in need.

546
00:48:06,010 --> 00:48:08,410
也许你该祈祷他不受伤害 对吗
Perhaps you should pray\nfor him to be unharmed, yes?

547
00:48:08,550 --> 00:48:10,740
- 求求你 还有希望\n- 再一次!
- Please, there's still hope...\n- Again!

548
00:48:23,500 --> 00:48:26,060
其实我对不老泉没有兴趣
I actually have no interest\nin the Fountain whatsoever,

549
00:48:26,200 --> 00:48:28,060
所以 如果你心意已定
so, if your heart is set,

550
00:48:28,200 --> 00:48:30,400
你可以随便把我放在哪里
you may drop me off\nanywhere you like.

551
00:48:30,540 --> 00:48:32,300
可以了 舵手
That'll be all, Quartermaster.

552
00:48:35,310 --> 00:48:38,800
你说的话像雾一样让我看不透
Your words surround you like fog\nand make you hard to see.

553
00:48:38,940 --> 00:48:42,780
那你呢 万能的黑胡子?
And what of you,\nthe mighty Blackbeard?

554
00:48:42,920 --> 00:48:45,680
他们说 即便是被砍头 你的身体
Beheaded they say.\nStill, your body swam

555
00:48:45,850 --> 00:48:49,290
还是绕着船游三圈\n然后爬上甲板
three times around your ship,\nthen climbed back onboard.

556
00:48:49,420 --> 00:48:52,020
而你现在却在害怕地逃命
And here you are, running scared.

557
00:48:52,660 --> 00:48:56,090
- 害怕?\n- 怕去不老泉
- Scared.\n- To the Fountain.

558
00:48:56,230 --> 00:48:59,250
舵手有预知能力
The Quartermaster\nsees things before they happen.

559
00:48:59,400 --> 00:49:03,890
他预见我的死亡\n所以命运开口了
He has foreseen my death,\nand so the fates have spoken.

560
00:49:04,000 --> 00:49:06,370
我的命数已定
The threads of destiny woven.

561
00:49:06,540 --> 00:49:09,470
你对命运有点可笑的迷信啊 老兄
You have a ridiculously\nhigh regard for fate, mate.

562
00:49:09,610 --> 00:49:11,240
- 那你呢?\n- 我?
- And you?\n- Me?

563
00:49:11,340 --> 00:49:15,640
我对算命这一套都表示怀疑...\n包括算我自己的
I'm skeptical of predicting\nany future... which includes me.

564
00:49:15,780 --> 00:49:21,580
与命运抗争比较傻\n但是我还是甘愿冒险
It'd be foolish to battle fate,\nbut I'd be tempted to cheat it.

565
00:49:21,690 --> 00:49:24,590
我会找到不老泉 你带我去
I will reach the Fountain.\nYou will lead me.

566
00:49:27,030 --> 00:49:31,020
那把刀就和你策划的暴动一样没有用
That knife will serve you no better\nthan the mutiny you devised.

567
00:49:31,160 --> 00:49:32,960
暴动很有效
Mutiny served me well.

568
00:49:33,100 --> 00:49:35,030
让我见到你了不是?
It gained me an audience with you.

569
00:49:37,040 --> 00:49:38,260
是啊
Aye.

570
00:49:39,670 --> 00:49:41,470
我警告你
To warn you.

571
00:49:42,440 --> 00:49:44,000
你的大副
Regarding your first mate,

572
00:49:44,140 --> 00:49:47,040
并不是她说的那个人
who pretends to be persons she is not.

573
00:49:47,650 --> 00:49:48,670
继续说啊
Do tell.

574
00:49:51,250 --> 00:49:53,050
她不是你女儿
She is not your daughter.

575
00:49:56,320 --> 00:49:59,380
你胆敢这么说我的亲生骨肉?
You dare to speak\nthusly of my flesh and blood?

576
00:49:59,520 --> 00:50:04,050
先生 那女人骗术高超
Sir, the woman is consummate\nin the art of deception.

577
00:50:04,200 --> 00:50:08,660
我很清楚\n是我不小心让她走上这条路
I know. As I mostly unwittingly\nset her on her wicked path.

578
00:50:08,800 --> 00:50:10,730
虽然我不能领功 说
Though I cannot claim credit

579
00:50:10,870 --> 00:50:13,840
她天生会骗人是我的功劳
for her existing abundance\nof natural talent.

580
00:50:15,840 --> 00:50:18,330
安洁莉卡 我钟爱的女儿
Angelica.\nMy beloved daughter,

581
00:50:18,480 --> 00:50:21,070
我这辈子做过唯一的真正的好事
the one true good thing\nI have done in this life,

582
00:50:21,210 --> 00:50:23,880
而你说 是你把她变成这样的?
and you claim to be the one\nwho corrupted her?

583
00:50:24,020 --> 00:50:28,040
先生 她很邪恶的
Sir, what she is is pure evil.

584
00:50:28,190 --> 00:50:30,590
比野兽还可怕
More to be feared than a wild beast.

585
00:50:30,720 --> 00:50:34,560
又饿又有尖牙的野兽
Hungry wild beast with gnashing teeth.

586
00:50:34,690 --> 00:50:36,720
来自地狱的饥饿野兽...
Vengeful, hungry from hell beast...

587
00:50:36,860 --> 00:50:39,020
- 父亲?\n- 甜美啊!
- Father?\n- Sweetness!

588
00:50:40,970 --> 00:50:42,520
没有必要伤害他 爸爸
No need to hurt him, Father.

589
00:50:42,670 --> 00:50:45,900
他会帮助我们 对吧 杰克
He will help us. Won't you, Jack?

590
00:50:46,040 --> 00:50:49,770
看见了吗? 即便是现在 她还是关心你的生死
You see? Even now,\nshe attends to your welfare,

591
00:50:49,910 --> 00:50:53,470
尽管你一直诋毁她
giving lie to the claims\nyou make of her.

592
00:51:01,050 --> 00:51:05,550
你会带我们到不老泉 对吧?
You will lead us to the Fountain. Yes?

593
00:51:06,360 --> 00:51:08,050
这么说吧
Put another way.

594
00:51:08,860 --> 00:51:12,260
要是我来不及赶到不老泉...
If I do not make it\nto the Fountain in time...

595
00:51:13,900 --> 00:51:16,890
...你也不能
...neither will you.

596
00:51:19,040 --> 00:51:23,170
我马上就看这些航海图 好吗?
I'll have a wee look-see at those charts\nstraight away then, shall I?

597
00:51:26,910 --> 00:51:28,170
先生
Sir.

598
00:51:31,050 --> 00:51:33,420
- 什么事?\n- 船长先生
- Aye?\n- Captain, sir,

599
00:51:33,550 --> 00:51:35,950
我听到不好的谣言 先生
I am unhappy to report rumors, sir,

600
00:51:36,090 --> 00:51:38,280
船员都在传 是关于我们的目的地的
among the crew,\nas to our destination.

601
00:51:39,460 --> 00:51:41,450
闭上你的狗嘴 给我滚
Shut your trap and make way.

602
00:51:45,460 --> 00:51:49,090
- 你想抗命吗\n- 我无意冒犯 船长...
- That's the way of it, then.\n- No disrespect, sir.

603
00:51:49,900 --> 00:51:52,730
他们在怕什么 快说出来 讲
What do the men fear?\nSay it. Speak the words.

604
00:51:53,470 --> 00:51:54,800
白帽湾
Whitecap Bay.

605
00:51:54,940 --> 00:51:58,070
是啊 白帽湾
Aye, Whitecap Bay.

606
00:51:58,180 --> 00:52:02,270
每一个没用的水手都怕这名字\n然后自以为是
And every worthless seaman\nfears the name, and rightly so,

607
00:52:02,410 --> 00:52:04,780
虽然很少人知道为什么
though few know why or dare to ask.

608
00:52:04,920 --> 00:52:06,540
谣言是真的吗...
Be the stories true?

609
00:52:06,720 --> 00:52:08,520
有话直说 吉布斯
Say what robs you of\nyour staunch heart, Gibbs,

610
00:52:08,650 --> 00:52:11,820
不然就当你自己痴人说梦
or forever leave it\nto the wider fields of fancy.

611
00:52:14,490 --> 00:52:16,120
人鱼 船长
Mermaids, Captain.

612
00:52:16,260 --> 00:52:18,020
是啊 人鱼
Aye. Mermaids.

613
00:52:18,160 --> 00:52:22,330
海怪 恶鱼 特爱吃人肉
Sea ghouls, devil fish,\ndreadful in hunger for flesh of man.

614
00:52:22,470 --> 00:52:26,030
我们就是要经过人鱼海域
Mermaid waters, that be our path.

615
00:52:26,170 --> 00:52:27,760
别丢了魂呐 吉布斯
Cling to your soul, Gibbs,

616
00:52:27,870 --> 00:52:30,800
听说人鱼会把人吃到...
as mermaids be given\nto take the rest...

617
00:52:32,100 --> 00:52:34,500
...只剩骨头
{\fnarial black\fs14\4a&H64&\fscx90\fscy110}...to the bone.

618
00:52:34,650 --> 00:52:37,810
稳住 稳住 鼓起勇气
Steady! Steady, men!\nFind your courage,

619
00:52:37,950 --> 00:52:39,850
不然就准备面对恐惧
or be ready to purpose your fear!

620
00:52:39,990 --> 00:52:42,390
自救啊!
Save yourselves!

621
00:52:44,960 --> 00:52:47,820
- 有人落水啦\n- 不 那是逃命的
- Man overboard!\n- Nay! A deserter.

622
00:52:47,960 --> 00:52:49,720
- 改变航向\n- 不行
- Come about.\n- Nay!

623
00:52:51,000 --> 00:52:54,830
先生们  我不会要求你们
Gentlemen, I shall not ask\nany more of any man than what

624
00:52:54,970 --> 00:52:59,460
做办不到的事\n但是我要问你们 我们是不是皇家海军?
that man can deliver, but I do ask this:\nAre we not king's men?

625
00:52:59,570 --> 00:53:01,040
是
Aye.

626
00:53:01,170 --> 00:53:03,940
- 是不是执行国王的命令?\n- 是
- On the king's mission?\n- Aye.

627
00:53:04,110 --> 00:53:08,340
我在经过我们的西班牙人眼中\n可没看到恐惧啊
I did not note any fear in the eyes\nof the Spanish as they passed us by.

628
00:53:08,480 --> 00:53:11,210
- 我们难道不是皇家海军?\n- 是!
- Are we not king's men?\n- Aye!

629
00:53:11,350 --> 00:53:14,280
是 准备 转向!
Aye! Hands all off, and bear away!

630
00:53:14,450 --> 00:53:17,390
向白帽湾进发!
Stave on ahead to Whitecap Bay!

631
00:53:19,020 --> 00:53:21,390
航向白帽湾!
Bear on, Whitecap Bay!

632
00:53:35,370 --> 00:53:36,860
来
Come.

633
00:53:37,010 --> 00:53:38,310
喝点小酒?
Little drink?

634
00:53:38,480 --> 00:53:41,710
美酒 音乐 蜡烛...
Wine, music, candlelight.

635
00:53:41,850 --> 00:53:44,080
这种事我们早就做过 杰克
I think we've traveled down\nthis road before, Jack.

636
00:53:44,220 --> 00:53:46,050
是啊 没错
Yes, we have.

637
00:53:47,020 --> 00:53:48,420
我记得很清楚
I remember it well.

638
00:53:50,260 --> 00:53:55,090
弯曲 扭曲 转身 摇摆 翻滚...
Winding, twisting and\nturning, gyrating, writhing.

639
00:53:55,230 --> 00:53:57,560
再不停地翻滚
Incessant writhing.

640
00:53:57,700 --> 00:53:59,560
记得圣多明哥吗?
Do you recall Saint Dominique?

641
00:54:01,000 --> 00:54:02,560
马提尼克岛
La Martinique.

642
00:54:02,700 --> 00:54:04,400
在圣多明哥我就想杀你了
I tried to kill you in Saint Dominique.

643
00:54:04,540 --> 00:54:06,300
没所谓啊
Either or.

644
00:54:07,110 --> 00:54:09,130
大副喝酒可不对啊
Hardly appropriate for a first mate.

645
00:54:09,270 --> 00:54:12,730
我是你第一个吗? 我一直在想
Was I the first? I've often wondered.

646
00:54:12,880 --> 00:54:17,110
你有求于人的时候的样子真迷人
You can be so charming\nwhen you want something, Jack.

647
00:54:17,250 --> 00:54:19,740
窍门是找出你想要什么
The trick is finding out what.

648
00:54:20,850 --> 00:54:22,950
是真相 对不对?
The truth, then, is it?

649
00:54:23,660 --> 00:54:26,150
黑胡子已经利用到了
Blackbeard has served his purpose.

650
00:54:26,290 --> 00:54:28,620
我们俩去不老泉
You and I can go to\nthe Fountain together,

651
00:54:28,760 --> 00:54:31,820
我们可以鸳鸯戏水  
where we shall bathe one another\nin equal shares of fame

652
00:54:31,960 --> 00:54:33,990
尽享欢愉
and other assorted debaucheries.

653
00:54:34,130 --> 00:54:37,120
而我会告诉你不老泉的仪式
And I'll tell you\nthe ritual of the Fountain.

654
00:54:37,270 --> 00:54:40,100
是啊 淫荡的仪式
Yes. The profane ritual.

655
00:54:42,810 --> 00:54:45,000
我能信任你吗 杰克?
Can I trust you, Jack?

656
00:54:45,140 --> 00:54:49,580
- 我需要你支持我\n- 最亲爱的安洁莉卡
- I need you on my side.\n- Oh, my dearest Angelica.

657
00:54:49,680 --> 00:54:53,140
我们是雌雄大盗啊 亲爱的
You and I are as\nthick as thieves, love.

658
00:54:53,290 --> 00:54:55,520
告诉我规则
Tell me the rules.

659
00:54:57,660 --> 00:55:01,320
不老泉的泉水
Water from the Fountain of Youth.

660
00:55:03,160 --> 00:55:06,600
人鱼闪亮的泪水...
The shimmering tear of a mermaid.

661
00:55:06,700 --> 00:55:10,030
庞德・里昂的银杯\nThe silver chalices of Ponce de Len.

662
00:55:11,970 --> 00:55:13,700
有了这些...
With these items...

663
00:55:13,840 --> 00:55:15,970
- 怎样?\n- 有了这些
- Yes?\n- With these items,

664
00:55:16,110 --> 00:55:19,510
你就可以汲取他人的寿命 杰克
you may take all the years\nof life from another, Jack.

665
00:55:21,780 --> 00:55:23,610
你知道那是什么意思
You know what that means.

666
00:55:23,720 --> 00:55:26,650
你跟我 我们不能自己去 
We cannot go alone, you and I.

667
00:55:26,790 --> 00:55:29,050
仪式需要一个牺牲者
The ritual requires a victim.

668
00:55:30,790 --> 00:55:34,660
- 这也太不幸了啊\n- 是的
- That is unfortunate.\n- Yes, it is.

669
00:55:35,660 --> 00:55:38,530
我对不老泉越发没兴趣了
I find my desire for the Fountain\ngreatly lessened.

670
00:55:39,930 --> 00:55:42,560
但是船上有你想要的东西
But there is something onboard\nyou do want.

671
00:55:48,340 --> 00:55:49,710
黑胡子怎么办?
What about Blackbeard?

672
00:55:49,840 --> 00:55:53,440
他在航图室 我们必须动作快
He's in the chart room.\nWe'll have to be quick.

673
