840
01:14:31,090 --> 01:14:34,540
跟我想的一样 不是这边
Just as I thought. Not this way!

841
01:14:36,620 --> 01:14:38,060
就是这边 对吧
This is the way, isn't it?

842
01:14:38,190 --> 01:14:41,030
当然 但是我们该绕路从东边走
'Course it is, but we\nshould go around to the east.

843
01:14:41,160 --> 01:14:43,030
那样就错过圣杯的地点了
That would take us out of\nthe path of the chalices.

844
01:14:43,160 --> 01:14:44,930
- 那我们再绕回来\n- 没时间了
- Well, then we'll circle back.\n- There is no time.

845
01:14:45,070 --> 01:14:46,730
是你坚持要带人鱼的
You're the one who insisted\non bringing the bloody mermaid.

846
01:14:46,870 --> 01:14:48,860
- 那你玩暴动也浪费时间了嘛\n- 你走路像姑娘
- Well, the mutiny didn't help.\n- You walk like a girl.

847
01:14:49,000 --> 01:14:51,100
- 到底谁像\n- 必须有人去
- You would know.\n- Someone must go.

848
01:14:52,170 --> 01:14:53,700
你是说分头行动?
You mean split up?

849
01:14:53,840 --> 01:14:56,740
你是说跳过去?我等不及要看看了
You mean jump?\nThis I cannot wait to see.

850
01:14:56,880 --> 01:15:00,870
斯派洛去 找到船 拿回圣杯
Sparrow will go.\nFind the ship, retrieve the chalices.

851
01:15:01,050 --> 01:15:03,020
斯派洛? 万一他一去不回了呢
Sparrow? What makes you\nthink he will come back?

852
01:15:03,120 --> 01:15:06,380
是啊 万一他一去不回了呢
Yes, what makes you think\nhe will come back?

853
01:15:06,520 --> 01:15:09,010
我们不能相信他 父亲 我去
We cannot trust him, Father. I'll go.

854
01:15:09,860 --> 01:15:11,590
她去
She'll go.

855
01:15:15,600 --> 01:15:16,960
离不老泉还有多远?
How much farther to the Fountain?

856
01:15:17,100 --> 01:15:18,790
我要没时间了
I'm running out of time.

857
01:15:20,770 --> 01:15:22,930
大约朝北走一天 沿着那条河
About a day's march north,\nfollowing that river,

858
01:15:23,070 --> 01:15:26,560
看到许多水塘时 就接近了
you'll get to a series of pools.\nThen you're close.

859
01:15:29,040 --> 01:15:30,310
你去
You will go.

860
01:15:33,210 --> 01:15:35,510
我就知道会这样
I was sure it would come to this.

861
01:15:49,100 --> 01:15:53,260
知道站在高处偶尔会有一种感觉
You know that feeling you get sometimes\nwhen you're standing in a high place?

862
01:15:53,400 --> 01:15:55,330
跳下去的冲动?
Sudden urge to jump?

863
01:15:57,240 --> 01:15:58,800
我可没有
I don't have it.

864
01:16:00,170 --> 01:16:01,730
我要圣杯
I need those chalices.

865
01:16:01,840 --> 01:16:04,330
开枪吧 免得我摔死
Shoot. Save me the bother of the fall.

866
01:16:04,480 --> 01:16:07,540
你去 再回来
You will go. You will return...

867
01:16:08,850 --> 01:16:10,840
...否则我杀了她
...or I will kill her.

868
01:16:13,650 --> 01:16:15,180
你不会杀自己女儿的
You won't kill your own daughter.

869
01:16:15,320 --> 01:16:18,120
舵手 再给我六把枪
Quartermaster, get me six more pistols,

870
01:16:18,260 --> 01:16:19,850
把子弹都清空 只留两把的
remove the shot from all but two,

871
01:16:19,990 --> 01:16:22,490
但别告诉我是哪两把
but do not tell me which two.

872
01:16:24,770 --> 01:16:27,360
你来选 斯派洛先生
You get to choose, Mr. Sparrow.

873
01:16:30,140 --> 01:16:31,330
不
No.

874
01:16:33,540 --> 01:16:34,570
不
No.

875
01:16:37,680 --> 01:16:40,510
- 是了\n- 你确定?
- Yes.\n- You're sure?

876
01:16:40,650 --> 01:16:42,120
当然
'Course I am.

877
01:16:50,320 --> 01:16:51,380
再来
Again.

878
01:16:52,890 --> 01:16:55,450
拜托 肯定都是空的
Please, they're not even loaded.

879
01:17:00,370 --> 01:17:01,660
再来
Again.

880
01:17:02,500 --> 01:17:04,400
如果你真这么想看她死
If you're so keen on killing her,

881
01:17:04,540 --> 01:17:06,940
- 不如让她跳?\n- 什么?
- why don't you just let her jump?\n- What?

882
01:17:07,710 --> 01:17:10,200
如果你跳了 又死了
If you jump and die,

883
01:17:10,340 --> 01:17:14,010
那就轮到她了
then she will have her chance.

884
01:17:14,150 --> 01:17:15,620
再来
Again.

885
01:17:18,850 --> 01:17:20,750
喂
Oi...

886
01:17:20,890 --> 01:17:24,760
如果我跳下去 能活吗
...if I jump, will I survive?

887
01:17:27,060 --> 01:17:28,430
娃娃
The doll.

888
01:17:44,750 --> 01:17:49,510
- 是的 现在能活了\n- 胡闹 我去
- Yes, now you will survive.\n- This is nonsense! I'm going!

889
01:18:08,240 --> 01:18:11,470
湿了 又湿了
Wet. Wet again.

890
01:18:13,770 --> 01:18:16,680
我们继续 正北去不老泉
We go on.\nDue north to the Fountain.

891
01:18:17,510 --> 01:18:18,880
演得好 父亲
Well played, Father.

892
01:18:20,610 --> 01:18:22,950
你知道哪两把上膛了 是吧
You knew which guns were loaded, right?

893
01:18:25,650 --> 01:18:27,640
当然 亲爱的
Of course, my love.

894
01:18:37,300 --> 01:18:40,030
有地图就好了
Be nice to have a map about now.

895
01:18:40,200 --> 01:18:41,830
有船就好了
Or a ship.

896
01:18:42,570 --> 01:18:46,300
停下 别动
Stop! Hold very still.

897
01:18:47,740 --> 01:18:51,270
别让它碰你的皮肤
Ye dare not let it touch your skin.

898
01:18:59,990 --> 01:19:03,250
怎么 老年人不能有点爱好吗
What? What be wrong with\nan older man having a hobby?

899
01:19:03,360 --> 01:19:05,920
还停着干什么 继续走啊
What are you stopping for, eh? Push on!

900
01:19:06,030 --> 01:19:08,260
- 前进\n- 死了以后有的是时间睡
- Push on!\n- You can sleep when you're dead.

901
01:19:08,360 --> 01:19:09,590
前进
Push on!

902
01:19:11,170 --> 01:19:14,530
幸运女神继续眷顾我们
Fortune continues to favor us.

903
01:19:42,300 --> 01:19:44,530
圣地亚哥号
The Santiago.

904
01:19:44,670 --> 01:19:47,400
船长是著名的庞德・里昂\nFamously captained by Ponce de Len.

905
01:19:50,170 --> 01:19:51,640
没有其他人了
There's no one there.

906
01:19:51,740 --> 01:19:52,760
好吧
Right, then.

907
01:20:27,440 --> 01:20:28,870
不能停下
We must not stop.

908
01:20:36,880 --> 01:20:38,680
你自己走
You will walk.

909
01:20:57,810 --> 01:20:59,970
我走不了
I cannot.

910
01:21:00,110 --> 01:21:01,900
不走就死
Walk or die.

911
01:21:08,350 --> 01:21:09,580
手臂环住我
Put your arms around me.

912
01:21:09,720 --> 01:21:13,120
- 我没要你帮忙\n- 但你需要
- I do not ask for help.\n- But you need it.

913
01:21:30,040 --> 01:21:34,340
- 我们不是赶时间吗\n- 别掉队
- We're in a hurry, yes?\n- Do not fall behind.

914
01:21:53,660 --> 01:21:55,420
停在这里 等我命令
Hold here 'til I say!

915
01:22:08,480 --> 01:22:10,340
真美
Such beauty.

916
01:22:10,480 --> 01:22:13,810
你一定是上帝的造物
Surely you're one of\nGod's own creations,

917
01:22:13,950 --> 01:22:16,880
而且不是那些诺亚方舟上没有一席之地的
and not a descendant\nof those dark creatures

918
01:22:17,020 --> 01:22:19,320
可怕怪物的后裔
who found no refuge on the Ark.

919
01:22:22,090 --> 01:22:24,220
真美
Such beauty...

920
01:22:25,490 --> 01:22:27,120
...但致命
...and yet deadly.

921
01:22:28,100 --> 01:22:31,550
- 致命?没有\n- 你袭击了我
- Deadly? No.\n- You attacked me.

922
01:22:31,700 --> 01:22:36,660
不 你不一样
No. You are different.

923
01:22:37,570 --> 01:22:38,800
不一样?
Different?

924
01:22:38,910 --> 01:22:42,930
不是吗 你保护了我
Are you not? You protect.

925
01:22:46,350 --> 01:22:47,400
难道你...?
Did you?

926
01:22:49,050 --> 01:22:51,850
你把我从爆炸中推开了
You pushed me down out of the way.

927
01:22:52,990 --> 01:22:57,480
- 看到不老泉了?\n- 还没 不过接近了
- You see the Fountain?\n- No, but we are close.

928
01:22:58,030 --> 01:22:59,890
把怪物带来 蒙住脸
Bring the creature.\nCover its head.

929
01:23:00,030 --> 01:23:02,020
她有名字
She has a name!

930
01:23:06,530 --> 01:23:08,060
请指教
Pray tell.

931
01:23:14,270 --> 01:23:16,170
她叫司瑞娜
She is Syrena.

932
01:23:57,120 --> 01:23:58,640
庞德・里昂\nPonce de Len.

933
01:24:02,320 --> 01:24:06,020
40个海盗40晚梦到的宝藏
If 40 pirates\ndreamt 40 nights of treasure,

934
01:24:06,190 --> 01:24:09,750
也比不上这间屋里的东西
it would not match\nthe contents of this room.

935
01:24:09,900 --> 01:24:11,450
你
You.

936
01:24:14,230 --> 01:24:16,030
- 你\n- 不...
- You.\n- No...

937
01:24:17,200 --> 01:24:19,470
- ...你\n- 我先来的
...you.\n- I was here first.

938
01:24:19,610 --> 01:24:23,630
- 你 为什么来这?\n- 黑胡子派我来的
- You, why are you here?\n- Blackbeard sent me.

939
01:24:23,780 --> 01:24:26,270
- 你呢?\n- 银圣杯
- Why are you?\n- Silver chalices

940
01:24:26,410 --> 01:24:29,780
- 给我的陛下\n- 哦 得了吧
- for my royal liege.\n- Oh, please.

941
01:24:31,020 --> 01:24:32,820
后退后退 要保持平衡
Back, back! We have to balance it out!

942
01:24:34,790 --> 01:24:37,380
船会整个滑下去
The whole ship will slide!

943
01:24:41,160 --> 01:24:42,790
好吧
Right, then.

944
01:24:42,930 --> 01:24:48,870
不如我们各选一样等重的东西?
What if we each choose an item\nof approximately equal weight?

945
01:24:51,510 --> 01:24:52,970
放回去
Put it back!

946
01:24:54,470 --> 01:24:56,530
什么也别碰
We touch nothing!

947
01:25:04,450 --> 01:25:05,420
那个呢?
What about that?

948
01:25:05,590 --> 01:25:07,950
圣杯
The chalices.

949
01:25:09,660 --> 01:25:11,180
喂 凭什么你先看
Oi! Why do you get to look first?

950
01:25:11,330 --> 01:25:13,020
好吧
Fine, then.

951
01:25:32,280 --> 01:25:33,840
- 一起\n- 一起
- Together.\n- Together.

952
01:25:36,550 --> 01:25:37,570
石头
Rocks.

953
01:25:38,650 --> 01:25:40,020
西班牙人
The Spanish.

954
01:25:40,720 --> 01:25:42,420
他们抢先了
They're ahead of us, mate.

955
01:25:43,320 --> 01:25:46,590
我要看一眼地图 如果是我担心的情况...
I shall have a look at that map.\nIf it's what I fear...

956
01:25:56,670 --> 01:25:58,900
奇怪 为什么他们没带走
I wonder why they left this behind.

957
01:26:01,880 --> 01:26:05,680
别碰地图
Don't touch the map.

958
01:26:11,020 --> 01:26:12,110
他们认识路
They know the path,

959
01:26:12,250 --> 01:26:16,150
不过我知道他们会在哪儿安营扎寨
but I can also see where\nthey'll most likely make camp.

960
01:26:29,600 --> 01:26:30,930
杰克
Jack!

961
01:26:34,110 --> 01:26:38,270
吉布斯 我正要去救你出狱
Gibbs, I was just on me way\nto break you out of jail.

962
01:26:40,210 --> 01:26:41,740
你偷了我的地图
You stole my map.

963
01:26:42,280 --> 01:26:44,750
好了 可以开始了
Right. Best be started.

964
01:26:47,790 --> 01:26:49,310
好
Ol?

965
01:27:06,710 --> 01:27:08,200
人鱼
Mermaids.

966
01:27:11,040 --> 01:27:13,980
小心 水塘很深
Careful, these pools run deep.

967
01:27:14,110 --> 01:27:17,680
如果她跑了 就前功尽弃 舵手
If she escapes, all is lost.\nQuartermaster.

968
01:27:19,320 --> 01:27:22,620
看啊
Look. Look!

969
01:27:24,190 --> 01:27:27,160
绑在这儿等死 被太阳暴晒
Staked out to die, to dry in the sun.

970
01:27:27,290 --> 01:27:30,890
只有半身浸在水里 无法活命
Only half in the water.\nNot enough to live,

971
01:27:31,060 --> 01:27:35,230
但能延缓死亡速度
but just enough to make the dying slow.

972
01:27:36,440 --> 01:27:37,460
好好想想
Think on it.

973
01:27:37,600 --> 01:27:41,010
你的族人被杀了\n就为了他们的眼泪
Your people, murdered,\nharvested for their tears.

974
01:27:41,140 --> 01:27:45,480
司瑞娜 你不想哭妈
Syrena, won't you cry?

975
01:27:46,350 --> 01:27:48,180
所有人都会死 连你也是
All die, even you.

976
01:27:48,320 --> 01:27:51,770
- 我听说快了\n- 听着...
- Soon, I hear.\n- Listen...

977
01:27:53,820 --> 01:27:55,690
听着
Listen.

978
01:27:55,820 --> 01:27:59,160
你听不到你的姐妹在尖叫吗
Can you not hear your sisters scream?

979
01:27:59,290 --> 01:28:01,730
你没听到么
Do you not hear them?

980
01:28:02,760 --> 01:28:05,560
我们只需要一滴眼泪
We need but one tear.

981
01:28:08,440 --> 01:28:09,730
下等生物!
Vile creature!

982
01:28:09,870 --> 01:28:12,460
- 把她的手指一根一根砍下来!\n- 掐死她!
- Chop off her fingers, one by one!\n- Choke her!

983
01:28:12,570 --> 01:28:15,200
把眼睛挖出来取出眼泪
Cut out the tears\nfrom behind the eyes!

984
01:28:15,340 --> 01:28:16,670
你怎么不说话
Where's your voice in this?

985
01:28:17,540 --> 01:28:20,570
也许等太阳出来她就会改变主意了
Maybe she'll have a change of heart\nwhen the sun rises.

986
01:28:20,710 --> 01:28:24,620
嗯 是的 她会被灼伤\n但是我等不及了
Oh, aye, she will burn,\nbut I cannot wait for the sun.

987
01:28:24,780 --> 01:28:26,480
也许我们应该烧死她
Perhaps we should build a fire.

988
01:28:26,590 --> 01:28:28,750
- 不行\n- 别反抗我 传道士
- No.\n- Do not contest me, cleric.

989
01:28:28,890 --> 01:28:31,950
- 你们不能折磨她\n- 我们只需要一滴眼泪
- You will not torture her.\n- We need only one tear.

990
01:28:32,130 --> 01:28:35,250
如果有必要\n我会把她身上的鳞片一片片拔下来
I will tear every scale\nfrom her body one by one if I see fit.

991
01:28:35,400 --> 01:28:36,950
如果这让你不快 一边祷告去吧
If that displeases you, go pray.

992
01:28:37,130 --> 01:28:40,220
我错了 不是所有的灵魂都能得到救赎\n你的就不行
I was wrong. Not every soul\ncan be saved. Yours cannot.

993
01:28:40,370 --> 01:28:43,230
看啊 伙计们\n一个曾经坚持信仰的人
Behold, gentlemen,\na man formerly of faith.

994
01:28:43,370 --> 01:28:46,270
你口中的下等生物 比你好百倍
That vile creature, as you call her,\nis worth a hundred of you.

995
01:28:46,410 --> 01:28:48,170
哎呦 你关心她
Oh, you care for her?

996
01:28:50,180 --> 01:28:52,200
你喜欢她
You fancy her.

997
01:28:53,880 --> 01:28:56,610
我看得清清楚楚 不用否认了
And do not deny what is\nclear to my eyes.

998
01:28:58,420 --> 01:28:59,540
问题是...
Question is...

999
01:29:02,720 --> 01:29:04,710
...她喜欢你么?
...does she fancy you?

1000
01:29:06,960 --> 01:29:10,560
我的天哪 她喜欢 我们走运了
By God, she does. We are in luck!

1001
01:29:11,970 --> 01:29:13,870
快流下眼泪...
Bring forth a tear...

1002
01:29:15,370 --> 01:29:17,890
...否则就见证这可怜人的死亡吧
...or witness the death\nof this poor soul.

1003
01:29:20,040 --> 01:29:23,480
司瑞娜 如果你能落泪
Syrena, if you could manage a tear,

1004
01:29:23,610 --> 01:29:25,200
我会很感激
I would be grateful.

1005
01:29:26,550 --> 01:29:28,140
难过 那就对了
Sadness, yes,

1006
01:29:28,280 --> 01:29:33,690
- 但还不是悲伤... 还不是\n- 爸爸!你不要动手
- but no sorrow... yet.\n- Not by your hand, Father!

1007
01:29:33,850 --> 01:29:36,480
时间和潮水不等人\n舵手
Time and tide wait for none.\nQuartermaster.

1008
01:29:48,800 --> 01:29:52,290
啊 人鱼真无情
Aye, mermaids are tough.

1009
01:29:52,440 --> 01:29:54,460
真不简单啊
The lot of them.

1010
01:29:54,610 --> 01:29:59,010
像她们一样把她绑起来\n然后把这东西丢掉
Tie her up like the others.\nAnd get rid of this.

1011
01:30:03,580 --> 01:30:06,580
- 你有信心么\n- 是的
- You are confident?\n- Yes.

1012
01:30:06,690 --> 01:30:09,680
我是女人 她也是
I am a woman. So is she.

1013
01:30:17,700 --> 01:30:20,720
你在玩什么把戏 杰克?\n居然跟巴博萨联手
What's your play, Jack?\nThrowing in with Barbossa.

1014
01:30:21,800 --> 01:30:23,600
有个女孩...
There is a girl...

1015
01:30:23,700 --> 01:30:26,930
...一个女人... 异性
...a female... of the opposite sex.

1016
01:30:27,040 --> 01:30:31,000
- 你什么时候没有过女人\n- 也许我应该说"落难少女"
- When is there not?\n- Perhaps I should say "damsel."

1017
01:30:31,140 --> 01:30:34,170
你在救一个落难少女\n好吧 这还是第一次
You're rescuing a damsel?\nWell, there's a first.

1018
01:30:34,310 --> 01:30:37,550
是的 就是 我可能在很久之前
Yes, but it's just that\nI may have caused said damsel

1019
01:30:37,680 --> 01:30:41,280
- 对这个落难少女造成了伤害\n- 快说
- some manner of harm many moons ago.\n- Out with it.

1020
01:30:41,390 --> 01:30:44,720
吉布斯 这是那个赛维尔女人
Gibbs, this is the woman from Seville.

1021
01:30:44,760 --> 01:30:48,860
啊 就是那个你假装爱她\n然后离开了 伤了她的心的那个
Ah, you pretended to love her,\nthen you left her and broke her heart.

1022
01:30:48,930 --> 01:30:53,630
更糟糕的是 我可能曾经有过\n稍微的 怎么说...
Worse. I may have had,\nbriefly, mind you...

1023
01:30:55,800 --> 01:30:58,970
...涟漪\n- 涟漪?
...stirrings.\n- Stirrings?

1024
01:30:59,070 --> 01:31:03,070
- 涟漪\n- 什么?你的意思是 感情?
- Stirrings.\n- What? Like feelings, you mean?

1025
01:31:03,210 --> 01:31:06,240
不不不 没到感情那种程度\n更像是...
No, no, no. Not quite all the way\nto feelings. More like...

1026
01:31:10,350 --> 01:31:11,980
好吧 感情 你个混蛋
All right, feelings, damn you.

1027
01:31:12,090 --> 01:31:16,780
但你还是离开她了\n真卑鄙
And you left her still.\nThat's low.

1028
01:31:18,220 --> 01:31:19,450
谢谢
Thank you.

1029
01:31:26,370 --> 01:31:27,800
只可智取不要蛮干
Stealth over force.

1030
01:31:27,970 --> 01:31:31,700
考虑到你的情况 接下来就交给我吧
I'll take it from here\non account of your condition.

1031
01:31:32,840 --> 01:31:34,700
你的假肢没被白蚁蛀坏了吧?
You don't have termites, do you?

1032
01:31:34,840 --> 01:31:36,810
杰克 感谢你的关心
I appreciate your concern, Jack,

1033
01:31:36,980 --> 01:31:39,470
但我要一直陪着你
but I'll be keeping\nyou company all the same.

1034
01:31:39,650 --> 01:31:42,710
待在这里 指挥官\n等我信号
Hold here, Lieutenant Commander.\nWait for my signal.

1035
01:32:14,680 --> 01:32:16,770
那里 那个人 他应该是头儿
There. That one.\nThat be the leader.

1036
01:32:16,920 --> 01:32:19,410
记住他的帐篷 因为那里...
Make note of his tent\nbecause that's where...

1037
01:32:20,890 --> 01:32:25,120
不 等等 天哪\n那一定就是它们了
No, wait. By God,\nthat must be them right there.

1038
01:32:28,630 --> 01:32:30,860
你的剑有股怪味
Your sword smells funny.

1039
01:32:31,030 --> 01:32:35,930
是的 涂了毒蟾蜍内脏的毒
Aye. Poison from the\ninnards of poisonous toads.

1040
01:32:36,070 --> 01:32:39,160
只要轻轻一划 几分钟之后你就死了
Just a scratch,\nyou're a dead man in minutes.

1041
01:32:39,310 --> 01:32:41,640
你介意把剑指向那边么
Would you mind pointing it\nthe other way?

1042
01:32:41,780 --> 01:32:43,540
我不喜欢蟾蜍
I don't like toads.

1043
01:32:48,410 --> 01:32:51,850
- 你在干嘛?\n- 研究逃跑路线
- What are you doing?\n- Planning an escape route.

1044
01:32:51,990 --> 01:32:56,080
- 你通常不都这么做么?\n- 是的
- Isn't that how you do it?\n- Yes.

1045
01:32:56,190 --> 01:32:59,320
但有时候我会... 随机应变
Or sometimes I just... improvise.

1046
01:33:26,320 --> 01:33:27,810
现在呢?
Now what?

1047
01:33:28,690 --> 01:33:31,210
我们就这么走出去 冷静 慢慢地
We stroll out, slow and steady.

1048
01:33:31,360 --> 01:33:33,190
像是自己人一样
Just like we belong.

1049
01:34:32,620 --> 01:34:36,890
- 司瑞娜 我很抱歉\n- 菲利普 你还活着
- I'm sorry, Syrena.\n- Philip, you're alive.

1050
01:34:37,020 --> 01:34:41,220
- 是的\n- 你回来救我了
- Yes.\n- You came for me.

1051
01:34:43,060 --> 01:34:44,590
为什么?
Why?

1052
01:34:46,700 --> 01:34:49,000
你是不同的 不是么?
You're different, are you not?

1053
01:34:51,200 --> 01:34:55,570
你不是很善良么?有同情心
Do you know not of kindness?\nCompassion?

1054
01:35:12,760 --> 01:35:14,750
悲伤的眼泪 从来没有过
Tears of sorrow, never.

1055
01:35:14,890 --> 01:35:17,330
人鱼太无情了
Mermaids be too tough for that.

1056
01:35:17,460 --> 01:35:19,620
但欢乐的眼泪...
But tears of joy...

1057
01:35:21,130 --> 01:35:23,570
他们说这种反而更有效
They say these be\nthe more potent anyway.

1058
01:35:23,670 --> 01:35:26,660
司瑞娜 相信我 我并不知情
Syrena, on my word,\nI had no part in this.

1059
01:35:27,940 --> 01:35:29,370
放了她\n你们现在不需要她了
Let her go.\nYou don't need her now.

1060
01:35:29,540 --> 01:35:32,480
放了她? 不行
Let her go? No.

1061
01:35:32,610 --> 01:35:35,600
把她绑好\n我们把她扔在这儿
Secure her bonds.\nWe leave her with her own.

1062
01:35:45,160 --> 01:35:47,150
逃跑路线是怎样的?
How's that escape route working?

1063
01:35:47,290 --> 01:35:50,260
现在是你随机应变的机会了
Here's your chance to improvise.

1064
01:35:50,360 --> 01:35:51,690
我也想呀
I'm attempting it.

1065
01:35:51,830 --> 01:35:54,660
我可能可以挣脱出一只手
I might be able to get a hand loose.

1066
01:35:54,800 --> 01:35:57,070
哎呦 你有刀 太好了
Oh, you got a knife.\nThat's very good.

1067
01:35:58,170 --> 01:35:59,700
还有更好的
Better.

1068
01:36:05,140 --> 01:36:06,410
我也要喝一口
I want one of those.

1069
01:36:11,120 --> 01:36:15,350
敬报仇 甜美畅快
Here's to revenge. Sweet and clear.

1070
01:36:15,490 --> 01:36:19,950
- 报仇?\n- 别装了
- Revenge?\n- Come, come, Hector.

1071
01:36:20,060 --> 01:36:21,490
如果你想要圣杯
If you wanted the chalices,

1072
01:36:21,630 --> 01:36:24,320
你已经知道它们被拿走了
you'd seen they were missing and gone.

1073
01:36:24,460 --> 01:36:27,630
你只是在坐等黑胡子
You were lying in wait, for Blackbeard.

1074
01:36:29,600 --> 01:36:32,830
乔治王 私掠船 假发
King George. Privateer. Wig.

1075
01:36:33,970 --> 01:36:35,410
演得太假了
Cheap theatrical facade.

1076
01:36:35,540 --> 01:36:38,410
- 我才不信\n- 那个晚上你不在场
- I'm not buying it.\n- You weren't there that night.

1077
01:36:38,540 --> 01:36:42,380
- 黑珍珠号丢了的那晚?\n- 被抢走了 不是丢了
- When the Pearl was lost?\n- Taken, not lost.

1078
01:36:44,980 --> 01:36:49,110
我们刚离开海地岛海岸就被攻击了
We were off the coast of Hispaniola\nwhen we came under attack.

1079
01:36:49,290 --> 01:36:52,720
没有挑衅 没有警告\n也没有谈判的机会
No provocation nor warning\nnor offer of parley.

1080
01:36:52,860 --> 01:36:55,520
我们被炮火攻击
We were peppered with cannon fire.

1081
01:36:56,660 --> 01:36:59,890
然后黑珍珠号下方的海水开始变浑浊
And then the sea beneath\nthe Pearl began to roil.

1082
01:37:01,430 --> 01:37:03,870
船晃得很厉害
The Pearl was pitching\nand yawing violently.

1083
01:37:04,000 --> 01:37:05,870
每个木板 每个栏杆
Every plank, every rail,

1084
01:37:06,010 --> 01:37:08,870
每个侧板 同时开始吱吱作响
every spar, all at once,\nbegan to creak.

1085
01:37:09,010 --> 01:37:12,030
船上的缆绳像有生命一样
The rigging had come to life.

1086
01:37:12,180 --> 01:37:14,870
我们的船居然跟我们自己作对...
Our own ship turned against us...

1087
01:37:15,010 --> 01:37:18,280
...绑着我们的船员\n像蛇一样绑着他们
...tangling the crew,\nwrapping around 'em like snakes.

1088
01:37:18,420 --> 01:37:20,820
还缠上了我的腿
And wrapping around me leg.

1089
01:37:20,990 --> 01:37:23,390
但我的手是自由的 手里还握着剑
But me arms were free\nand me sword was to hand.

1090
01:37:23,520 --> 01:37:27,050
我才是船的主人 不是黑胡子
I am the master of me ship,\nnot Blackbeard.

1091
01:37:27,190 --> 01:37:30,690
我是自己命运的主人 不是黑胡子
I am the master of my fate,\nnot Blackbeard.

1092
01:37:31,700 --> 01:37:34,060
所以我做了我需要做的事
So I did what needed done.

1093
01:37:40,910 --> 01:37:42,840
我活下来了
I survived.

1094
01:37:44,410 --> 01:37:48,610
所以... 你不是冲着泉水去的
So... you're not after the Fountain.

1095
01:37:48,750 --> 01:37:52,410
我才不管乔治王\n或是什么乱七八糟的谣言
I care not for King George\nor tavern yarns

1096
01:37:52,550 --> 01:37:54,780
说可以治愈四肢
that give hope for a healed limb.

1097
01:37:56,420 --> 01:38:00,090
我甚至愿意牺牲我的左手\n换取杀了黑胡子的机会
But I'd give my left arm\nfor a chance at Blackbeard.

1098
01:38:00,290 --> 01:38:03,260
- 不是你的右手\n- 我需要我好用的手
- Not your right?\n- I need me good arm

1099
01:38:03,400 --> 01:38:08,060
用毒箭剑穿他的心脏
to drive my poisoned blade\nthrough his heart.

1100
01:38:09,040 --> 01:38:11,470
伙计 你会有机会的
I'll see you get the chance, mate.

1101
01:39:30,220 --> 01:39:31,550
囚犯要逃跑啦
The prisoner's escaping.

1102
01:39:38,820 --> 01:39:41,520
他要跑了!散开! 找到他!
He's escaping!\nFan out! Find him!

1103
01:39:41,660 --> 01:39:42,750
走!快走!
Go! Go!

1104
01:39:44,830 --> 01:39:47,700
别开枪!我要抓活的!
Hold your fire! I want him alive!

1105
01:39:55,910 --> 01:39:57,880
我觉得那就是你的信号了
I figured that was the signal.

1106
01:40:40,950 --> 01:40:44,450
- 走! 准备出发!\n- 敌人很快就会找到我们
- Go! Prepare to move out!\n- The enemy is soon upon us.

1107
01:40:46,190 --> 01:40:49,130
杰克 抱歉没拿到圣杯\n但我在赶时间
I'm sorry about the chalices, Jack,\nbut I've an appointment to keep.

1108
01:40:49,260 --> 01:40:52,250
- 我不会回去拿的\n- 没这个必要
- I'll not be going back.\n- No need.

1109
01:40:52,400 --> 01:40:55,420
- 要不要来一杯?\n- 我们去不老泉喝
- Shall we have a drink?\n- We'll drink at the Fountain.

1110
01:41:13,790 --> 01:41:17,350
为什么我们每次见面\n你都是拿着什么东西指着我?
How is it we can never meet\nwithout you pointing something at me?

1111
01:41:18,560 --> 01:41:20,460
斯派洛 你拿到圣杯了么?
You brought the chalices, Sparrow?

1112
01:41:20,590 --> 01:41:23,190
是的 喂!
Aye. Oi!

1113
01:41:26,670 --> 01:41:29,790
- 你还带了个朋友\n- 是的
- I see you brought a friend.\n- I did.

1114
01:41:29,940 --> 01:41:33,170
那个独腿男人也在附近 是吧?
And the one-legged man, he is near.\nAye?

1115
01:41:33,310 --> 01:41:34,710
是
Aye.

1116
01:41:35,510 --> 01:41:36,530
好了...
Now...

1117
01:41:36,680 --> 01:41:39,510
在我把它们给你之前我有一两个条件
Before I go just handing them over,\nI do have one or two conditions.

1118
01:41:39,650 --> 01:41:41,700
- 说\n- 首先
- Name them.\n- Firstly,

1119
01:41:41,850 --> 01:41:44,210
把我的指南针还我\n不 不 那是其次
I'll be having me compass back.\nNo, no, that's secondly.

1120
01:41:44,350 --> 01:41:46,610
首先 你得遵守承诺
Firstly, upon your word,

1121
01:41:46,720 --> 01:41:48,710
不能伤害安洁莉卡
you will bring no harm to Angelica.

1122
01:41:48,850 --> 01:41:51,220
斯派洛 我不想做任何对你有益的承诺
I'll make no vows\nto the likes of you, Sparrow.

1123
01:41:51,360 --> 01:41:53,830
但承认我根本就不想伤害她
But it costs me nothing to admit

1124
01:41:53,960 --> 01:41:56,830
对我并没有任何损失
that she was never in harm's way.

1125
01:41:57,460 --> 01:41:59,660
那么其次 比首先更重要的是
Secondly then, priorly firstly,

1126
01:41:59,800 --> 01:42:01,430
把我的指南针还我
I will be having me compass back.

1127
01:42:02,340 --> 01:42:04,360
拜托了? 那是我应得的
Please? I do deserve it.

1128
01:42:04,500 --> 01:42:08,000
你知道抓住那只死肥猪有多难么?
Do you have any idea how difficult\nit was to catch that filthy pig?

1129
01:42:08,140 --> 01:42:10,510
不是那个大只的 那个四条腿的
Not the big one,\nthe four-legged one.

1130
01:42:13,950 --> 01:42:17,710
谢谢 第三 胡子先生
Thank you. And thirdly, Mr. Beard,

1131
01:42:17,850 --> 01:42:20,550
我有的时候 虽然不是很经常
there are times, not very often,

1132
01:42:20,690 --> 01:42:23,780
也会反省我犯下的恶行
when I do reflect\nupon my heinous misdeeds.

1133
01:42:23,960 --> 01:42:28,220
首当其冲就是\n我有多么对不起吉布斯先生
Chief among them, I note how poorly\nI have treated Mr. Gibbs,

1134
01:42:28,360 --> 01:42:31,020
- 我忠诚的大副\n- 对啊! 现在你才想起这茬...
- my loyal first mate.\n- Aye! Now you bring it up...

1135
01:42:31,160 --> 01:42:33,860
我让他在监狱中腐烂\n根本不在乎他
Left him to rot in jail, I did.\nDidn't care.

1136
01:42:34,000 --> 01:42:38,660
现在也不 但重点是\n你得放他走
Still don't. But, point being,\nyou must let him go free.

1137
01:42:40,510 --> 01:42:43,870
- 就这样?\n- 是的
- Is that it?\n- I think so.

1138
01:42:44,010 --> 01:42:46,700
快决定吧 不然猪就要跑了\n你们得自己去找圣杯 祝你们好运
Quick, or the pig runs,\nand good luck getting those chalices.

1139
01:42:46,750 --> 01:42:48,210
杰克 如果是你 我一定会...
Jack, if it's all the same to you,\nI'd be just as...

1140
01:42:48,350 --> 01:42:49,680
好的
Done.

1141
01:42:49,780 --> 01:42:51,010
放了那头猪
Release the swine.

1142
01:42:56,790 --> 01:43:00,050
其实如果你们不介意\n我可以跟你们一段...
Perhaps, if you don't mind,\nI could tag along with you folk for a...

1143
01:43:02,800 --> 01:43:05,060
伙计 这会指引你奔向自由
This will lead you to freedom, mate.

1144
01:43:11,740 --> 01:43:14,600
我发誓应该就在这附近
I could have swore it was\nsomewhere right around here.

1145
01:44:44,700 --> 01:44:47,060
我们不能停下
We must not stop.

1146
01:45:04,380 --> 01:45:05,820
死路
Dead end.

1147
01:45:06,820 --> 01:45:08,750
死路
Dead. End.

1148
01:45:09,460 --> 01:45:10,850
死路
Dead end.

1149
01:45:11,890 --> 01:45:14,860
杰克 我开始有种\n你不知道自己在往哪儿走的感觉
Jack, I'm starting to think\nyou don't know where you're going.

1150
01:45:15,660 --> 01:45:18,490
大家都说旅程比目的地更重要
It is not the destination\nso much as the journey, they say.

1151
01:45:19,700 --> 01:45:21,170
拜托把圣杯给我
Chalices, if you please.

1152
01:45:33,180 --> 01:45:34,700
后退
Stand back.

1153
01:45:57,070 --> 01:45:58,630
杰克...
Jack...

1154
01:45:58,770 --> 01:46:00,710
...你有没有 真的...
...have you ever, in fact...

1155
01:46:00,840 --> 01:46:06,330
...亲眼见到...不老泉?
...seen with your own eyes...\nthe Fountain of Youth?

1156
01:46:06,510 --> 01:46:08,670
抱歉 你能重复一遍你的问题么?
I'm sorry, could you\nrepeat the question, please?

1157
01:46:08,850 --> 01:46:10,310
舵手
Quartermaster.

1158
01:46:11,250 --> 01:46:12,220
不 不!
No, no!

1159
01:46:15,890 --> 01:46:18,020
等等 等等!
Wait, wait! Wait.

1160
01:46:21,290 --> 01:46:25,750
"生命...之水"
"Aqua... de Vida."

1161
01:47:05,100 --> 01:47:07,630
斯克鲁姆先生...
Master Scrum...

1162
01:47:07,770 --> 01:47:10,640
- 你可不可以...?\n- 阁下?
...do you mind?\n- Squire?

1163
01:48:09,330 --> 01:48:11,330
真漂亮
So beautiful.

1164
01:48:50,810 --> 01:48:53,440
斯派洛 我要成为第一个尝泉水的人
Sparrow, I'll be the first\nto taste those waters.

1165
01:48:57,920 --> 01:48:59,510
爸爸
Father.

1166
01:49:02,790 --> 01:49:05,090
独腿男人
The one-legged man.

1167
01:49:07,630 --> 01:49:11,590
- 你带他来了\n- 我会这么做么?
- You brought him here.\n- Would I do that?

1168
01:49:11,730 --> 01:49:13,820
爱德华・汀奇!
Edward Teach!

1169
01:49:13,970 --> 01:49:17,270
你在公海上犯下的罪
For crimes committed on the high seas,

1170
01:49:17,400 --> 01:49:21,270
我以国王陛下授予我的权力...
by the authority granted me\nby His Majesty the King...

1171
01:49:21,410 --> 01:49:24,600
...伴随着很大一部分的个人成就感...
...and with a goodly amount\nof personal satisfaction...

1172
01:49:24,740 --> 01:49:27,800
...我宣布你现在将被法院拘留
...I hereby place you\nin the custody of the court,

1173
01:49:27,950 --> 01:49:31,280
成为我的囚犯
and declare you to be my prisoner.

1174
01:49:32,320 --> 01:49:35,840
我玩完了 是吧?
My trick's out, is that it?

1175
01:49:35,990 --> 01:49:40,430
所犯的罪行包括但不局限于\n海上抢劫 叛国
Such crimes do include, but are not\nlimited to, piracy, treason,

1176
01:49:40,530 --> 01:49:44,690
谋杀 还有最恶劣的是虐待
murder, torture of\nthe most heinous sort,

1177
01:49:44,830 --> 01:49:48,770
包括残忍的偷盗了一只\n用过的扭曲的多毛的右脚
including the brutal theft of one used,\ntwisted, hairy right leg.

1178
01:49:49,540 --> 01:49:54,230
你... 敢与此剑为敌?
You... dare face this sword?

1179
01:49:54,410 --> 01:49:56,840
离你的船这么远的地方? 当然
This far away from your ship? Aye.

1180
01:49:56,980 --> 01:50:01,710
嗯 我感到我颈后命运的冷酷呼吸
Aye. That be the cold breath\nof fate I feel down my nape.

1181
01:50:01,850 --> 01:50:07,510
但我将以主之名最后一战
But I'll have one last fight, by God.

1182
01:50:07,650 --> 01:50:09,380
杀了他们!
Kill 'em all!

1183
01:50:11,020 --> 01:50:12,820
稍等一下
Hang on a minute.

1184
01:50:12,960 --> 01:50:16,860
我... 我想弄明白点事情
I just... I just need\nto understand something.

1185
01:50:17,000 --> 01:50:20,360
好吧 所以 你们要打他们
Right, so, you will fight against them,

1186
01:50:20,500 --> 01:50:21,830
他们要打你们
they will fight against you.

1187
01:50:21,970 --> 01:50:25,660
只因为他想杀他?
All on account of him\nwanting to kill him?

1188
01:50:25,800 --> 01:50:29,740
有道理么? 就是说嘛
Where is the sense? Exactly.

1189
01:50:29,880 --> 01:50:33,610
要我说 让他们俩自己打去
I say, let them fight\neach other while we lay back,

1190
01:50:33,780 --> 01:50:37,220
而我们就靠边看着 喝点小酒\n赌赌输赢!
watch, have a drink,\nplace some wagers!

1191
01:50:38,320 --> 01:50:39,610
好啊
Aye.

1192
01:50:42,190 --> 01:50:43,810
- 杀了他们!\n- 绝不留情!
- Kill 'em!\n- No quarter!

1193
01:51:14,290 --> 01:51:15,950
滚开!
Get off me!

1194
01:51:48,920 --> 01:51:49,950
斯克鲁姆 圣杯!
Scrum, the chalices!

1195
01:51:52,090 --> 01:51:53,220
还有眼泪! 跟我来!
And the tear! Follow!

1196
01:51:57,230 --> 01:51:58,420
打啊!
Fight!

1197
01:51:59,330 --> 01:52:02,890
交出来 人鱼的眼泪\n这才是好孩子
Hand it over. The tear.\nThere's a good lad.

1198
01:52:03,000 --> 01:52:05,330
比起你 我更怕她
I'm more afraid of her\nthan I am of you.

1199
01:52:10,880 --> 01:52:13,280
交出来\n这才是好孩子
Hand it over.\nThere's a good lad.

1200
01:52:16,650 --> 01:52:20,380
- 拜托把圣杯给我\n- 杰克 抱歉
- The chalices, if you please.\n- Sorry, Jack.

1201
01:52:20,550 --> 01:52:24,780
我告诉过你 我需要多点寿命\n现在 用你的就可以了
I told you, I need years.\nAnd now, yours will do.

1202
01:52:32,700 --> 01:52:33,930
斯克鲁姆!
Scrum!

1203
01:52:55,590 --> 01:52:57,050
司瑞娜...
Syrena...

1204
01:53:00,790 --> 01:53:03,560
主啊 你不能带她走
Oh God, you will not take her.

1205
01:53:03,700 --> 01:53:08,660
如果你带走了她 请让她回来
If you have taken her,\nyou will give her back.

1206
01:53:08,800 --> 01:53:11,170
让她回来...
Give her back...

1207
01:53:11,300 --> 01:53:14,170
让她回来 拜托
Give her back, please. Please.

1208
01:53:37,760 --> 01:53:40,530
我还以为命运会让我多打一会儿呢 嗯?
I expected fate\nto put up more of a fight, eh?

1209
01:53:57,380 --> 01:54:01,180
我把你打倒了 如果是我就笑不出来了
I will not have that smile\non your face as I strike you down.

1210
01:54:02,590 --> 01:54:05,680
看看吧 爱德华・汀奇
Take a gander, Edward Teach.

1211
01:54:36,220 --> 01:54:39,520
这片土地将永远属于光荣的
This land is hereby forever\nclaimed in the glorious name

1212
01:54:39,690 --> 01:54:42,250
乔治王陛下名下...
of His Majesty King George...

1213
01:54:48,500 --> 01:54:51,440
来人呐 记下这人的勇敢
Someone make a note\nof that man's bravery.

1214
01:54:58,410 --> 01:55:02,140
女士 请把圣杯给我\nSeorita, the chalices, por favor.

1215
01:55:18,830 --> 01:55:24,500
只有上帝才能赐予永恒的生命\n而不是这异教的水
Only God can grant eternal life,\nnot this pagan water.

1216
01:55:35,550 --> 01:55:39,040
来人 把这亵渎神的庙毁掉!
Men, destroy this profane temple!

1217
01:55:41,790 --> 01:55:43,120
不老泉!
The Fountain!

1218
01:55:57,170 --> 01:55:58,690
你个白痴
You are a fool.

1219
01:55:58,840 --> 01:56:02,140
你在这里所寻找的东西\n只有信仰才能给你
You seek in this place\nwhat only faith can provide.

1220
01:56:02,240 --> 01:56:04,800
信仰? \n信仰给你光明让你看见
Faith? In faith,\nthere is light enough to see

1221
01:56:04,910 --> 01:56:07,170
却也足够黑暗让你失明
but darkness enough to blind.

1222
01:56:10,780 --> 01:56:13,050
这是为什么?
What devilry is this?

1223
01:56:17,020 --> 01:56:19,620
- 这是为了黑珍珠号\n- 你做了什么?
- For the Pearl.\n- What have you done?

1224
01:56:23,160 --> 01:56:25,560
安洁莉卡! 不要! 剑上有毒!
Angelica! Don't! It's poison!

1225
01:56:30,200 --> 01:56:32,530
如果不是有点毒液优势
I'm not such the fool\nto take on Blackbeard

1226
01:56:32,670 --> 01:56:36,070
我才不会蠢到去单挑黑胡子
without a little venomous advantage.

1227
01:56:37,380 --> 01:56:38,870
杰克!
Jack!

1228
01:56:50,690 --> 01:56:52,750
我宣布黑胡子的船和船员
I claim Blackbeard's ship and crew,

1229
01:56:52,890 --> 01:56:56,330
以及这把剑\n是对我失去的肢体的赔偿!
and this sword,\npayment for my missing limb!

1230
01:57:10,740 --> 01:57:12,140
抓好了! 拉!
Hang on! Pull!

1231
01:57:57,420 --> 01:57:59,790
别浪费了我的眼泪
Do not waste my tear.

1232
01:58:29,250 --> 01:58:31,380
喝下它 这杯是有眼泪的
Drink this.\nThis one has the tear.

1233
01:58:31,520 --> 01:58:33,510
- 你得喝下另一杯\n- 不!
- You must drink the other.\n- No!

1234
01:58:34,290 --> 01:58:37,520
我没办法同时救你们俩\n你们中有一个人得牺牲自己
I cannot save you both.\nOne of you must sacrifice.

1235
01:58:38,460 --> 01:58:41,560
爸爸 你喝吧 以拯救你的灵魂
You take it, Father, for your soul.

1236
01:58:43,600 --> 01:58:49,040
汀奇船长\n她快死了 你得救救你女儿
Captain Teach, she's dying.\nYou must save your daughter.

1237
01:58:50,210 --> 01:58:53,010
这杯是夺去生命的?
This one takes life?

1238
01:58:53,140 --> 01:58:55,010
这杯有眼泪是赐予生命的?
This one has the tear and gives life?

1239
01:58:55,150 --> 01:58:56,410
是的 快啊!
Aye, hurry!

1240
01:59:05,320 --> 01:59:09,590
安洁莉卡...\n救救我 我的孩子
Angelica...\nSave me, my child.

1241
01:59:11,500 --> 01:59:12,930
不
No.

1242
01:59:21,640 --> 01:59:23,070
爸爸 我爱你
I love you, Father.

1243
01:59:36,050 --> 01:59:37,680
等等
Wait a minute.

1244
01:59:39,860 --> 01:59:42,690
事实上 可能搞反了
In fact, it might have been\nthe other way around.

1245
01:59:43,530 --> 01:59:47,360
这杯有眼泪 那个是另一杯
This cup had the tear,\nthat one had the other bit.

1246
01:59:47,470 --> 01:59:48,730
骗子!
Trickster!

1247
01:59:48,870 --> 01:59:50,730
- 恶魔!\n- 爸爸!
- Devil!\n- Father!

1248
01:59:57,740 --> 01:59:59,270
你个混蛋! 你怎么能这样?
You bastard! How could you?

1249
02:00:00,280 --> 02:00:01,750
你爸爸救了你
Your father saved you.

1250
02:00:01,880 --> 02:00:04,410
他的灵魂也许这样就能被救赎了 恩?
Perhaps his soul is now redeemed, eh?

1251
02:01:05,210 --> 02:01:07,340
你受伤了
You are hurt.

1252
02:01:09,550 --> 02:01:11,480
只是身体上
In body only.

1253
02:01:13,150 --> 02:01:17,380
我的心很平静... 因为你
My mind is at peace...\nbecause of you.

1254
02:01:18,460 --> 02:01:21,320
- 我?    \n- 是的
- Me?\n- Yes.

1255
02:01:22,330 --> 02:01:24,730
我迷失过
I was lost.

1256
02:01:25,700 --> 02:01:30,360
那海风 那潮汐...
The wind, the tides...

1257
02:01:30,500 --> 02:01:33,560
...它们本会改变一个人的信仰
...they ought to renew a man's faith.

1258
02:01:35,140 --> 02:01:37,070
但对于我来说 只有你能
But for me, only you.

1259
02:01:37,980 --> 02:01:41,710
菲利普 我可以救你
Philip, I can save you.

1260
02:01:41,850 --> 02:01:44,820
你只需要开口
You need only ask.

1261
02:01:46,250 --> 02:01:51,050
- 我只追寻一件事\n- 什么?
- I seek but one thing.\n- What is that?

1262
02:01:52,060 --> 02:01:54,420
原谅
Forgiveness.

1263
02:01:54,560 --> 02:01:57,890
如果不是因为我 你根本不会被抓
If not for me, you would\nnever have been captured.

1264
02:01:58,030 --> 02:01:59,690
开口吧
Ask.

1265
02:02:01,570 --> 02:02:03,400
原谅我?
Forgive me?

1266
02:02:28,530 --> 02:02:29,750
我恨你
I hate you.

1267
02:02:29,890 --> 02:02:32,230
救了你一命的家伙?
The bloke who saved your life?

1268
02:02:32,360 --> 02:02:35,560
我拥有的寿命是从我亲生父亲那里偷来的!
The years I possess,\nstolen from my own father!

1269
02:02:35,700 --> 02:02:38,730
我只是帮了黑胡子做了\n任何父亲都会做的事
I only helped Blackbeard do what\nany father should have done.

1270
02:02:38,870 --> 02:02:42,070
你既残忍又无知
You are cruel and ignorant.

1271
02:02:45,780 --> 02:02:49,580
一把手枪 一颗子弹
One pistol, one shot.

1272
02:02:49,710 --> 02:02:51,940
在我饿死前自杀?
To kill myself before I starve?

1273
02:02:52,080 --> 02:02:53,640
亲爱的 我不相信你
There's no trusting you, love.

1274
02:02:53,790 --> 02:02:56,250
再说了 这是繁忙的贸易路线
Besides, this is a\nwell-traveled trade route.

1275
02:02:56,390 --> 02:02:57,980
你可以给过往船只打信号
You can signal a passing ship.

1276
02:02:58,120 --> 02:03:01,580
或是饮弹自尽 随你便
Or you can just bite the\nproverbial bullet, as it were.

1277
02:03:01,730 --> 02:03:03,320
那我又要怎么挣脱这些绳索?
And how will I get free\nof these bonds?

1278
02:03:03,460 --> 02:03:06,230
你半个小时之前就挣脱了绳索
You broke free of your bonds\nhalf an hour ago,

1279
02:03:06,330 --> 02:03:09,160
只是在等着突袭的最佳时刻
waiting for the precise moment\nto pounce.

1280
02:03:11,870 --> 02:03:13,560
杰克 承认吧
Admit it, Jack.

1281
02:03:13,670 --> 02:03:17,610
- 你还爱我\n- 如果你有个姐妹和一条狗
- You still love me.\n- If you had a sister and a dog,

1282
02:03:17,740 --> 02:03:20,040
我会选择那条狗
I'd choose the dog.

1283
02:03:20,210 --> 02:03:23,580
宝藏!有个装满珠宝的箱子!
Treasure!\nThere is a chest with jewels!

1284
02:03:23,680 --> 02:03:25,950
拥有控制风和潮汐的力量的珠宝!
Jewels with the power\nto rule the wind and tide!

1285
02:03:26,080 --> 02:03:29,180
- 你在胡编乱造!\n- 等等...
- You're making that up!\n- Wait...

1286
02:03:29,990 --> 02:03:33,690
我怀孕了 你的
I am with child. Yours.

1287
02:03:34,930 --> 02:03:36,330
我不记得我们曾经...
I don't recall that we ever had...

1288
02:03:36,460 --> 02:03:39,190
- 你当时醉了!\n- 我从没有那么醉过
- You were drunk!\n- I've actually never been that drunk.

1289
02:03:39,330 --> 02:03:40,460
等等!
Wait!

1290
02:03:42,330 --> 02:03:44,390
我有话想对你说
There is something I want to say to you.

1291
02:03:44,570 --> 02:03:48,730
从我们一见面起我就想说
Something I wanted to say\nfrom the moment we first met.

1292
02:03:49,670 --> 02:03:50,800
说吧
Go on, then.

1293
02:03:53,140 --> 02:03:54,480
我爱你
I love you.

1294
02:03:58,050 --> 02:03:59,880
我也是
As do I.

1295
02:04:00,020 --> 02:04:03,480
一直是 永远也会是
Always have. Always will.

1296
02:04:07,990 --> 02:04:09,480
我得走了
I gotta go.

1297
02:04:09,630 --> 02:04:10,650
杰克!
Jack!

1298
02:04:12,960 --> 02:04:14,560
还没完呢!
This is not over!

1299
02:04:15,630 --> 02:04:16,690
杰克!
Jack!

1300
02:04:26,280 --> 02:04:27,770
打偏了!
Missed!

1301
02:04:43,060 --> 02:04:46,090
复仇成功
The Revenge is mine.

1302
02:04:52,770 --> 02:04:54,240
先生...
Sir...

1303
02:04:56,710 --> 02:04:58,570
我们在甲板下找到了这个
We found this below decks.

1304
02:05:24,670 --> 02:05:26,930
所有人!顺风而上!
All hands!\nPly to windward!

1305
02:05:27,070 --> 02:05:30,630
动作快点 你们这些人渣!
Get cracking,\nye blooming cockroaches!

1306
02:05:33,340 --> 02:05:35,940
王室对我不薄
The Crown served me well.

1307
02:05:36,080 --> 02:05:39,070
但现在 以海神和天空之神之名...
But now, by the gods of sea and sky...

1308
02:05:39,220 --> 02:05:43,310
...朝托尔图加出发!
...make way for Tortuga!

1309
02:05:54,430 --> 02:05:57,600
吉布斯 你个混蛋 痴迷的老水手\n你来了!
Gibbs, you filthy, besotted shellback,\nyou made it!

1310
02:05:57,740 --> 02:05:59,290
是!
Aye!

1311
02:05:59,440 --> 02:06:01,030
我相信我们联手
And I trust we managed a profit

1312
02:06:01,170 --> 02:06:05,340
- 得到了点好处?\n- 好好看清楚
- from our joint enterprise?\n- Feast your eyes.

1313
02:06:10,410 --> 02:06:12,940
指南针直指向目标
The compass led me straight and true.

1314
02:06:13,080 --> 02:06:15,080
黑胡子那些看船的家伙们呢?
What of Blackbeard's men\nguarding the ship?

1315
02:06:15,190 --> 02:06:19,090
我用了跟新几内亚那次一样的招数
I employed the selfsame maneuver\nwe perfected in New Guinea.

1316
02:06:19,190 --> 02:06:23,290
扔下整艘船其实挺可惜的
Seemed a shame to leave\nan entire fleet behind.

1317
02:06:23,430 --> 02:06:25,490
是挺可惜的
Shame indeed.

1318
02:06:37,440 --> 02:06:38,810
我恨那只猴子
I hate that monkey.

1319
02:06:38,940 --> 02:06:42,380
所以 黑珍珠号...\n我们应该怎样把她弄出来呢?
So, the Pearl...\nAny idea how to get her out?

1320
02:06:42,510 --> 02:06:45,540
我们需要一把十字弓\n一个沙漏 三只羊
We shall need a crossbow,\nan hourglass, three goats.

1321
02:06:45,680 --> 02:06:48,710
我们中得有人学会吹小号\n同时另一个人这样子...
One of us must learn to play the trumpet\nwhilst the other one goes like this...

1322
02:06:49,220 --> 02:06:52,520
- 我认识一个有羊的人\n- 很好 我可以这样子
- I know a man with a goat.\n- Good. I can go like this.

1323
02:06:55,160 --> 02:06:56,820
杰克 我想问...
Jack, I have to ask...

1324
02:06:56,960 --> 02:06:59,830
你当时有圣杯 泉水和眼泪...
You had the chalices,\nthe water, the tear...

1325
02:06:59,960 --> 02:07:02,490
也许你能永远不老
You could have lived maybe forever.

1326
02:07:02,630 --> 02:07:04,600
吉布斯 不老泉确实会测试你
The Fountain does test you, Gibbs.

1327
02:07:04,770 --> 02:07:07,670
但最好还是不要知道自己的\n最后一刻是什么时候
But better to not know\nwhich moment may be your last.

1328
02:07:07,810 --> 02:07:09,830
生命的每一刻
Every morsel of your entire being

1329
02:07:09,970 --> 02:07:13,070
都是无止尽的奥秘
alive to the infinite mystery of it all.

1330
02:07:13,210 --> 02:07:15,740
再说了 谁说我不会不老?
And who's to say\nI won't live forever, eh?

1331
02:07:15,880 --> 02:07:19,010
我发现了不老泉呢
Discoverer of the Fountain of Youth.

1332
02:07:19,150 --> 02:07:22,050
一切都充满不确定性 吉布斯
I have no say in it, Gibbs.

1333
02:07:22,190 --> 02:07:24,180
那才是我要的海盗生涯
It's a pirate's life for me.

1334
02:07:25,120 --> 02:07:26,610
懂了么?
Savvy?





